sheBridgeMib.name: sheBridgeMib

revisions.description: Change contens of mstp-notifications. Change limit for sheQueueWeight - 0 is not valid. Change sequence of bits for sheLagPortPartnerAdminState and sheLagPortPartnerOperState. Define size for sheIgmpProviderControlProxyIpAddress.

Change syntax for sheBridgePortMcastGroupPackageList. Change definition for SheLagStateType. Add new entrys in sheBridgePort-table to configure special features. Add new values for BridgePortUsage-Type. Add new table and controlgroup for sheBridgeMacProfile for feature IpoA. Add new entry sheVlanDefaultGateway in sheVlanTable to support IpoA mode. New Rule portFlowControl03(18) to set PVID on the basis of Ethertyp and portindex. New genericRule type defined. Add value ranges to meteringprofile-table.

Add new values in SheDhcpRelayAgentOptionType to support simplified Dhcp Relay Agent. Change SheHostConfigurationProtocolType to support DHCP and PPPoE on the same port. Add entry in sheVlanTable for additional PPPoE-Provider-Index. New control request to configure this entry. Modify description for sheBridgeBaseOuterPVID. Add new rules and new Attributes to sheRuleAndMetering-table. New entry sheIgmpMaxJoinedSubscriber in sheIgmpBase. Add also new controlrequest to modify this entry.
Define a value range for sheIgmpMaxJoinedSubscriber. Add comment for activation of IPoA-mode (BridgePortTable).

Change sheRuletable. Add some entrys and change descriptions. All new values only used for generic rule types (expert mode)! New value in sheIgmpGroupTable for information about currently supplied card's.

Add new values in sheBridgeBase-Group. Add values to sheBridgePortCreated-notification. Delete value CpuPermit from sheFdb-Table. Change range and default for sheErpDomainWaitToRestoreTime. Change range for sheDhcpRelayRemoteId to 6..64.
Change description for BridgePortMode.

Add comment for autogenerate of valid macaddress for IPoA mode. Add sheVlanPPPoEProviderIndex to VlanCreated-Trap. Add controlrequest-type modifyRule and corresponding notification. Change name and description for sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeSinceLastMembRep to sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeFirstMembRep.
sheArpVlanTable and sheArpVlanControl node were added in to support the vlan arp flooding control.
Take over by Gerd Barchmann for R2.5.
Use sheVlanIndex as index for sheDhcpFloodVlanIdTable and sheIgmpFloodVlanTable. Add new features from SHE R2.3 MIB version 152 (BridgeBase, Vlan, Fdb).
Merge update for new SHE R2.3 MIB-Version 153. Merge update for new SHE R2.3 MIB-Version 154.
Minor changes for backward compatibility. Add bridgePort-mode PPPoA. Add index parameter to sheUmasControl-Group. Merge new data for IGMP from SHE MIB release 155 for R2.3.

Change parameter sequence for some bridgePort-Trap's. Modify comment for sheReducedQueuePriorityTable. Add new values to sheVLanTable for protocol handling configuration of DHCP, PPPoE ,ARP and IGMP on vlan base.

Correct range for sheIgmpProviderQueryInterval, IgmpProviderQueryResponseInterval, sheIgmpProviderStartupQueryInterval and IgmpProviderLastMemberQueryInterval. Some of the new values in sheVlanTable for protocol handling on vlan base removed again. The other ons will be supported with release R2.5.1. Remove not usable BridgePort-Tagging modes! Add an VlanServiceType value. Add vlan identifier to the list of available values for sheBridgeBaseCircuitIdFormat and sheBridgeBaseRemoteIdFormat. Correct Description for QueuePerformanceCounters. Introduce new sheBridgeIUProfileTable for IU specific Bridge-Configurations. Merge with SHE2.3 MIB release 156.
Modify Range and description for sheBridgePortMaxLearnPermitCount.
Modify index value for sheCebsVirtualMacAddressTable.

New Release R2.5.2: Modify maximum range for sheBridgePortMaxLearnPermitCount. Expand MAT for TCom requirement. Expand QueueConfiguration per card. Modify MeterProfileConfiguration for more flexible configuration of policing/shaping for DS/US.
Modifications after review of AFI MIB release SHE R2.5.2. New attribute in sheLagGroupTable.

Add attribute to sheVlan-table to support McastFlood configuration. Modify description for support of sheVlanMulticastPermission attribute in R2.5.2. Modify descriptions for support of some sheDhcpProviderTable attributes in R2.5.2. Merge MIB 159 for late feature of R2.3 for common MIB version (BridgePortTable, UMAS).

Modify configuration for DsShaping per Port/Queue. Add parameters to sheBridgePortTable for individual multicast configuration. Modify descriptions for support of some sheDhcpProviderTable attributes in R2.5.2.
Remove not longer needed shaping parameter from sheMeterProfileTable.

Add new detailed ReqResult-Values. Remove support for sheIgmpMaxJoinedSubscribers. Add new value sheDhcpBcastTranslationDs to dhcp provider table. Change default value for sheVlanServiceType. Enable/disable MAT per Vlan. Mat per BridgePort is not longer supported.
Correct only descriptions regarding SHE version change R2.5.2->R2.6.
Correct description for textual convention SheDhcpRelayAdminStateType. Correct syntax for sheIgmpProfileVlanInnerVlanId. Correct range for sheMatBaseDslamId.

Correct ranges for shapingprofile parameters. Merge MIB release for SHE R2.4 -> -sheBridgePortIgmpSubscriberAccessMode added into sheBridgePortTable. -sheIgmpProviderVlanMulticastLimitation added into sheIgmpProfileTable. -sheIgmpProfileVlanForkingMode added into sheIgmpProfileVlanTable, controlgroup and trap. -sheErpDomainGlobalGroup and sheErpDomainGlobalControl added.
Correct objectlist for sheIgmpProfileVlanEntryCreated-trap.
Modify description for sheVlanServiceTagOnly. Merge modification from new R2.4 MIB proposal (not supported by R2.6).
R2.7. Minor descriptional changes. Expand index of sheMatTable.

New release SHE R2.8 supported. Add functions in sheBridgePortTable and BridgeBase. Add option to sheDhcpRelayAgentOptionType. Add functions in sheDhcpProviderTable. Add functions in sheIgmpProfileTable. Add support for IGMPv3.

Correct syntax for sheMatControlReqResult. Modify index value for sheMatTable again. Update parameter for IGMPv3 support. Modify parameter description for sheDhcpBcastTranslationDs and sheDhcpCebsMacTranslation. Modify parameter names for sheBridgePortPriorityMap usage. Correct syntax and description for sheIgmpMaxJoinedGroup.
Restore Vlan-Configuration for DHCP again. Rename IgmpSourceIpTable.
Add parameter for NodeIdentifier to DHCP provider configuration. Add vlan-id for DHCP snooping table (CO hiX13600). Modify parameter list for Bridge CircuitId and RemoteId configuration.

Made config for DhcpUseInnerTag global and separate config for PPPoE providers. Made config for IgmpUseInnerTag global. Expand BridgePortPriorityOptions configuration. Expand sheMatTranslationMode with mode thsNoIndexOffset.
Modify PortPriorityOptions parameter. Modify RuleGenericMatchAction parameter.
Expand BridgePort multicast configuration. Modify RuleGenericMatchAction parameter and add new RuleTablePattern. Modify ShapingProfileAssignment.
Correct sheIgmpModeModified trap. Remove last modifications for RuleGenericMatchAction parameter. Define new fixedRuleTypes for feature Policing per COS, Protokoll or Vlan.

Modify AC feature for MC traffic on bridgeport and igmp provider side. Expand IGMP port statistic's for CA and AC counter. CEBS support by SHE system only if CXU types CXU_B, CXU_B1 or CXU_C are used (like R2.7)!

Add parameter to BridgeIUProfile for used MAT type selection. Add new BridgePortMCastTable + controlgroup to support new R2.8 Mcast parameters. Add/Modify parameters to IgmpBase, IgmpProvider and IgmpGroup to support IGMPv3 in R2.8. Add detailed failure returncode definitions to ReqResult enum. The scheduled support release is not defined yet.

Correct description for sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlRequest and sheIgmpGroupControlRequest. Modify description for BridgeBase CircuitId and RemoteId. Add parameter to vlan table for configuration of servicename. Modify description for sheBridgePortPriorityMapTable: default profile with index 1 can't be deleted. Add new parameter sheBridgePortMCastMinUCBandwithLimit to bridgePort MCast configuration table. Merge vlan parameter for uplink vlan translation from R2.6 RP2.

New parameters for CardQueueConfigurationTable to support HQS mode. New EthertypMapping configuration to support EthertypVlan mapping per bridgeport. New IpAntispoofing configuration to support IPAS per bridgeport. Expand parameter list for StaticIp configuration. Define new fixedRuleTypes for feature RateLimiting IGMP. New dhcp base parameter for StationMove feature enable/disable. Move ReplaceVlanTag parameter to IUPofileTable.

Correct stationMoveModified trap. Correct syntax and description for sheBridgePortMCastAllowedVlanIdList. Assign DscpPriorityMapProfile via IUProfile configuration (add on). Correct CardQueueConfiguration table parameter list. Modify ShapingProfile assignment for 'perDslPort' usage.

Move some R2.8 Mcast releated bridgeport parameter from sheBridgePortMCastConfigTable to new sheIgmpBridgePortProviderTable under the sheIgmp subtree -> new group sheIgmpBridgePortConfig. Move some new R2.8 parameters from sheIgmpProvileTable to sheIgmpProfileVlanTable.
Modify syntax of sheIgmpPortGroupsStpIpAddress. The sheBridgePortReplaceVlanTag is used again for enable/disable the feature.

Correct possible number accesible premium and non-premium Igmp groups per bridgePort. Correct the default mc bandwith limit per bridgePort to 'unlimited' - switch off ac feature. Correct description of sheBridgePortControlReplaceVlanTag.
Correct IGMP trap parameter list: - sheIgmpProfileVlanEntryCreated - sheIgmpProfileVlanEntryModified. Correct syntax for parameters from sheCardQueueConfigurationTable.
Modify remarks from ACI. Add new parameter to dhcp provider table. Modify comment for DhcpAdminState settings.

Correct description of bridgePort inner and outer priorityOption setting. Correct description of queue weight and watermark settings. Correct description of igmp stats controlRequest commands. Remove 0 as possible value for sourceIp setting during igmpGroup configuration. Correct description of sheLagGroupCollectorMaxDelay - any modification will be ignored. Add new group sheBridgeExtResidentialConfig only supported by hiX5608!

Modify syntax for sheDhcpFloodVlanEnabled to enable the flooding for DHCP and PPPoE separatly. Expand IgmpProvider and IgmpGroup table with new parameter DefaultSourceIpList. New command for FdbTable refresh. New command for MatTable refresh. Add new value for circuitId/RemoteId definition. Expand length of circuitId and remoteId bridgeBase parameter.

Correct description and default for sheIgmpProviderVlanMulticastLimitation. Move sheIgmpProviderDefaultSourceIdList to corresponding sheIgmpProfileVlanTable. Modify second index for sheIgmpPortGroupTable and add parameters. Expand range for sheBridgeBaseControlMaxHostName to 64. Correct default value sheBridgePortLeaveMode.

R2.8 BFR2.0 MIB-Update. Correct wrong syntaxtype of sheErpDomainGlobalControlMacLearningDelay. Modify syntax for sheBridgePortMaxLearnPermitCount. Add missed parameter in sheFdbTable. DHCP provider config does still not need VlanId config (like R2.6). Add new cistPort parameter for support only by 5608 R1.3. Add new FdbControl parameter for support only by 5608 R1.3.
Correct BridgeBaseModified trap parameter list. No change inside NE. Define default values for queue watermark settings.
Remove not supported R2.8 parameter for BaseMaxIpUni command and trap.
Correct description for sheBridgePortMode. Correct description for sheVlanTunnelingL2Protocol and sheVlanDefaultGateway. Expand valid range for sheBridgePortIpAddressPermitCount to 64.
Correct CircuitId and RemoteId format according TR101. Modify syntax for sheBcscVendorSpecific. Correct usable range for sheRuleControlTosPattern.
Add new table for dynamic UMAS configuration per VLAN (CR#003659). Remove wildcard option from fdbTable refresh commands.

sheBridgeMib.contactinfo: Gerd Barchmann COO BCS BBA RD SDE gerd.barchmann@nsn.com +49 3834 555654
sheBridgeMib.description: This MIB contains all needed informations about bridgePorts and all supported she bridgeing features.

SheMcastLeaveMode.name: SheMcastLeaveMode
SheMcastLeaveMode.description: The leave mode of a bridgeport for mcast traffic.

SheBridgePortIpAsModeType.name: SheBridgePortIpAsModeType
SheBridgePortIpAsModeType.description: The possible settings for bridgeport based IpAntispoofing.

SheBridgeIUProfileUsedMATBasisType.name: SheBridgeIUProfileUsedMATBasisType
SheBridgeIUProfileUsedMATBasisType.description: Used type for selection of MAT basis per IU.

SheMeterProfileUseParametersType.name: SheMeterProfileUseParametersType
SheMeterProfileUseParametersType.description: This type definition defines a bit-map for using the meterprofile parameter settings. If the corresponding bit is set to one the parameters should be used.

SheDhcpRelayAdminStateType.name: SheDhcpRelayAdminStateType
SheDhcpRelayAdminStateType.description: telegram handling for DHCP and PPPoE relay: valid telegrams are handled, invalid telegrams are dropped snoop: valid telegrams are forwarded, invalid telegrams are dropped bridge: valid telegrams are forwarded, invalid telegrams are forwarded handling explanation: dhcpPppoeRelayRelay -> dhcp and Pppoe use mode relay dhcpPppoeRelaySnoop -> dhcp use mode relay and Pppoe use mode snoop Attention: The value up(1) and down(2) are only valid for she R1.5, R2.0 and R2.3. Release R2.5 and later will only accept value's 4..12

SheDhcpUseTagForProtocolsType.name: SheDhcpUseTagForProtocolsType
SheDhcpUseTagForProtocolsType.description: Used for configuration of global DHCP and PPPoE useTag settings.

SheIgmpVlanMode.name: SheIgmpVlanMode
SheIgmpVlanMode.description: Configure VLAN mode for the system. This configuration is only functions when system is configured in double tagging mode.

SheIgmpVersionType.name: SheIgmpVersionType
SheIgmpVersionType.description: To configure the supported Igmp version on provider vlan base.

SheIgmpPortGroupsFiltermodeType.name: SheIgmpPortGroupsFiltermodeType
SheIgmpPortGroupsFiltermodeType.description: filter-mode may be either INCLUDE or EXCLUDE.

SheCardQueueModeType.name: SheCardQueueModeType
SheCardQueueModeType.description: The possible queue modes a DSL IU can use.

SheMatTranslationModeType.name: SheMatTranslationModeType
SheMatTranslationModeType.description: The attribute descripes, which format for MAC address translation will be used.

SheDhcpFloodingType.name: SheDhcpFloodingType
SheDhcpFloodingType.description: To configure the flooding of DHCP and/or PPPoE packets per vlan.

SheBridgeMaxIpAddressType.name: SheBridgeMaxIpAddressType
SheBridgeMaxIpAddressType.description: Used inside bridge configuration for maxIp support.

SheBridgeIdType.name: SheBridgeIdType
SheBridgeIdType.description: Used as type defintion for BridgeBase and BridgePort CircuitId and RemoteId configuration. The following predefined types are available: %B -> portstring (like 'iuslot'/'iuport') %M -> mac address %N -> NodeId or Hostname (only if individuell NodeIdentifier not available) %T -> (dsl) line type (adsl, vdsl, shdsl) %S -> slot %P -> port %R -> subport/servicename or Vlan ID (only if subport/servicename not available) %V -> unique vcc id %b -> unique bridgeport id %p -> vpi number %c -> vci number %E -> ethernet priority %v -> vlan ID %s -> slot number as printed on shelf %t -> tc-layer type (atm, eth) Useful separation characters: space . , ; / - : * It is also allowed to place free text. Predefined types will be replaced by NE with the requested information. The maximum total length of a resulting Id string is still 63 byte (overlaps will be cut off)!

sheBridgeBaseMode.name: sheBridgeBaseMode
sheBridgeBaseMode.description: The general operating mode of the bridge.

sheBridgeBaseTaggingMode.name: sheBridgeBaseTaggingMode
sheBridgeBaseTaggingMode.description: The general tagging mode of the bridge.

sheBridgeBaseMirrorPort.name: sheBridgeBaseMirrorPort
sheBridgeBaseMirrorPort.description: The Mirror port of the system. That is a sheBridgePortIndex and it could only be used on ports with bridgePortUsage = uplink. This value should be 0 if no mirror-port is configured in the system

sheBridgeBaseOuterPVID.name: sheBridgeBaseOuterPVID
sheBridgeBaseOuterPVID.description: The default PVID of the outer Vlan used by the switch fabric in case of doubleTag-Mode or if a frame with priority tag is received and no other rule to change the vlan tag will match.

sheBridgeBaseOuterPriority.name: sheBridgeBaseOuterPriority
sheBridgeBaseOuterPriority.description: The default .1p-Priority of the outer vlan in case of doubleTag-Mode.

sheBridgeBaseCircuitIdFormat.name: sheBridgeBaseCircuitIdFormat
sheBridgeBaseCircuitIdFormat.description: The default value should be: '%N %t %S/%P:%p.%c' -> when ATM/DSL is used '%N %t %S/%P:%v' -> when Ethernet/DSL is used It is up to the customer, to select the needed informations from this list and use a meaningfull combination. Also a combination with free text is possible. The maximum total length of a resulting circuitId is still 63 byte (overlaps will be cut off)!

sheBridgeBaseSharedVlanLearning.name: sheBridgeBaseSharedVlanLearning
sheBridgeBaseSharedVlanLearning.description: Enable or disable the feature SharedVlanLearning in the NE.

sheBridgeBaseRemoteIdFormat.name: sheBridgeBaseRemoteIdFormat
sheBridgeBaseRemoteIdFormat.description: The default value is: '%M' It is up to the custoumer, to select the needed informations from this list and use a meaningfull combination. Also a combination with free text is possible. The maximum total length of a resulting remoteId is still 63 byte (overlaps will be cut off)!

sheBridgeBaseStagTPID.name: sheBridgeBaseStagTPID
sheBridgeBaseStagTPID.description: The TPID of the service tag if doubleTag is enabled.

sheBridgeBaseMacAntiSpoofing.name: sheBridgeBaseMacAntiSpoofing
sheBridgeBaseMacAntiSpoofing.description: Enable or disable the feature MacAntiSpoofing in the NE.

sheBridgeBaseRoutingMode.name: sheBridgeBaseRoutingMode
sheBridgeBaseRoutingMode.description: residential or unrestricted the feature Routing Mode of BridgeBase in the NE.

sheBridgeBaseMaxHostName.name: sheBridgeBaseMaxHostName
sheBridgeBaseMaxHostName.description: the maximum length of hostname for circuit-id or remote-id.

sheBridgeBaseDlfFilter.name: sheBridgeBaseDlfFilter
sheBridgeBaseDlfFilter.description: The policy of DLF (destination lookup failur) unicast packets from uplink. Enable DLF filter -> destination-mac unknown unicast towards subscriber ports blocked Disable DLF filter -> destination-mac unknown unicast towards subscriber ports allowed default:enable

sheBridgeBaseUnknownMuticastFilter.name: sheBridgeBaseUnknownMuticastFilter
sheBridgeBaseUnknownMuticastFilter.description: The policy of unknown multicast packets from uplink. It can be set to enable when routing mode is residential default: enable in R2.0, disable in R2.3 / R2.5.x Possible values: disable(0), enable(1) -> means enable both directions! enableDs(2) -> enable only downstream direction enableUs(3) -> enable only upstream direction

sheBridgeBaseIpoaArpReqInterval.name: sheBridgeBaseIpoaArpReqInterval
sheBridgeBaseIpoaArpReqInterval.description: The interval of ARP resolution for IPoA Bridgeport Default: 0 If the value is 0, it means NE does not send any arp request to an ipoa provider edge router after the router ip address is resolved. Thus, if the ipoa provider edge router's MAC address is changed, packet uses wrong MAC address, unused one, for ipoa provider edge router.

sheBridgeBaseMaxIpUNI.name: sheBridgeBaseMaxIpUNI
sheBridgeBaseMaxIpUNI.description: This is the maximum number of possible IpAddresses (DHCP or fixed IP) per UNI Port. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgeBaseControlRequest.name: sheBridgeBaseControlRequest
sheBridgeBaseControlRequest.description: setBridgeMode: sheBridgeBaseControlMode setBridgeTaggingMode: sheBridgeBaseControlTaggingMode setBridgeMirrorPort: sheBridgeBaseControlMirrorPort setBridgeOuterVlanDefaults: sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPVID sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPriority setBridgeCircuitIdFormat: sheBridgeBaseControlCircuitIdFormat setBridgeSharedVlanLearning: sheBridgeBaseControlSharedVlanLearning setBridgeRemoteIdFormat: sheBridgeBaseControlRemoteIdFormat setBridgeStagTPID: sheBridgeBaseControlStagTPID setBridgeMacAntiSpoofing: sheBridgeBaseControlMacAntiSpoofing setBridgeRoutingMode: sheBridgeBaseControlRoutingMode setBridgeMaxHostName: sheBridgeBaseControlMaxHostName setBridgeDlfFilter: sheBridgeBaseControlDlfFilter setBridgeUnknownMulticastFilter: sheBridgeBaseControlUnknownMulticastFilter setBridgeIpoaArpReqInterval: sheBridgeBaseControlIpoaArpReqInterval

sheBridgeBaseControlStatus.name: sheBridgeBaseControlStatus
sheBridgeBaseControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheBridgeBaseControlTimer.name: sheBridgeBaseControlTimer
sheBridgeBaseControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheBridgeBaseControlReqResult.name: sheBridgeBaseControlReqResult
sheBridgeBaseControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheBridgeBaseControlTimeStamp.name: sheBridgeBaseControlTimeStamp
sheBridgeBaseControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPVID.name: sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPVID
sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPVID.description: The PVID of the outer Vlan in case of doubleTag-Mode.

sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPriority.name: sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPriority
sheBridgeBaseControlOuterPriority.description: The default .1p-Priority of the outer vlan in case of doubleTag-Mode.

sheBridgeBaseControlCircuitIdFormat.name: sheBridgeBaseControlCircuitIdFormat
sheBridgeBaseControlCircuitIdFormat.description: It is up to the customer, to select the needed informations from this list and use a meaningfull combination. Also a combination with free text is possible. The maximum total length of a resulting circuitId is still 63 byte (overlaps will be cut off)!

sheBridgeBaseControlSharedVlanLearning.name: sheBridgeBaseControlSharedVlanLearning
sheBridgeBaseControlSharedVlanLearning.description: Enable or disable the feature SharedVlanLearning in the NE.

sheBridgeBaseControlRemoteIdFormat.name: sheBridgeBaseControlRemoteIdFormat
sheBridgeBaseControlRemoteIdFormat.description: It is up to the customer, to select the needed informations from this list and use a meaningfull combination. Also a combination with free text is possible. The maximum total length of a resulting remoteId is still 63 byte (overlaps will be cut off)!

sheBridgeBaseControlStagTPID.name: sheBridgeBaseControlStagTPID
sheBridgeBaseControlStagTPID.description: The TPID of the service tag if doubleTag is enabled

sheBridgeBaseControlMacAntiSpoofing.name: sheBridgeBaseControlMacAntiSpoofing
sheBridgeBaseControlMacAntiSpoofing.description: Enable or disable the feature MacAntiSpoofing in the NE.

sheBridgeBaseControlRoutingMode.name: sheBridgeBaseControlRoutingMode
sheBridgeBaseControlRoutingMode.description: residential or unrestricted the feature Routing Mode of BridgeBase in the NE.

sheBridgeBaseControlMaxHostName.name: sheBridgeBaseControlMaxHostName
sheBridgeBaseControlMaxHostName.description: the maximum length of hostname for circuit-id or remote-id.

sheBridgeBaseControlDlfFilter.name: sheBridgeBaseControlDlfFilter
sheBridgeBaseControlDlfFilter.description: The policy of DLF unicast packets from uplink.

sheBridgeBaseControlUnknownMulticastFilt.name: sheBridgeBaseControlUnknownMulticastFilter
sheBridgeBaseControlUnknownMulticastFilt.description: The policy of unknown multicast packets from uplink. It can be set to enable when routing mode is residential default: enable in R2.0, disable in R2.3 / R2.5.x Possible values: disable(0), enable(1) -> means enable both directions! enableDs(2) -> enable only downstream direction enableUs(3) -> enable only upstream direction

sheBridgeBaseControlIpoaArpReqInterval.name: sheBridgeBaseControlIpoaArpReqInterval
sheBridgeBaseControlIpoaArpReqInterval.description: The interval of ARP resolution for IPoA Bridgeport Default: 0 If the value is 0, it means NE does not send any arp request to an ipoa provider edge router after the router ip address is resolved. Thus, if the ipoa provider edge router's MAC address is changed, packet uses wrong MAC address, unused one, for ipoa provider edge router.

sheBridgeBaseControlMaxIpUNI.name: sheBridgeBaseControlMaxIpUNI
sheBridgeBaseControlMaxIpUNI.description: This is the maximum number of possible IpAddresses (DHCP or fixed IP) per UNI Port. New parameter with SHE R2.8. Not configurable with current release!

sheBridgePortEntry.name: sheBridgePortEntry
sheBridgePortEntry.description: One entry for every bridgePort of the system.

sheSubLayerIndex.name: sheSubLayerIndex
sheSubLayerIndex.description: IfIndex of the underlaying Interface in the interface-table, Also LAG-bridgePorts will be modeled in the interface table.

sheSubLayerCircuit.name: sheSubLayerCircuit
sheSubLayerCircuit.description: Only used in case the bridgePort represents a PVC, otherwise equal 0. This value represent the the index for sheAdslVccTpTable, sheXdslVccTpTable or sheShdslVccTpTable depending on ifType of underlaying physical interface. This index was build by the following rule: index = (SubLayerIndex << 4) + Vcc-Number Lowest value for she is 0x0651 (ifIndex = 101 and Vcc-Number 1). Highest value for she is 0x6EC8 (ifIndex = 1772 and Vcc-Number 8).

sheBridgePortPVID.name: sheBridgePortPVID
sheBridgePortPVID.description: The PVID of the port. Possible range is 1-4093 for subscriber ports. This value points to the corresponding vlanIndex of the sheVlanTable. The default value for subscriber bridgePorts is the ifIndex of the underlaying physical interface (sublayerindex). Uplink and LAG bridgePorts use PVID 1 as default.

sheBridgePortUsage.name: sheBridgePortUsage
sheBridgePortUsage.description: defaults: Dsl PVC : subscriber Adsl special: vccAggregatorNotUsed Uplink : upLink Lag : notUsed If upLink-Port is aggregated, the upLink state moves to aggregated and the Lag moves to uplink. If a physical bonding is used (Shdsl 4wire/6wire/8wire done over shdsl configuration, m-pair bonding), the master bridgeport changes his usage to physbondedSubscriber and all other members to notUsed. If a gbond bonding is used (via she-bonding-mib configuration), the master bridgeport-entry of the new bonding port changes his usage to bondingSubscriber and all other members of bonding port to bondingNotUsed. For the feature singleMacMultipleVcc, it is possible to aggregate two or more single VCC's of one physical adsl-link to the vccAggregator. The usage of the single PVC - bridgeports (subscriber) could be set to vccAggregated and the special bridgeport change his usage from vccAggregatorNotUsed to ..Used in that case. It is also possible to set this special bridgeport usage directly and in that case all bridgeports with identical sublayerindex will change her usage to vccAggregated. This configuration has additional restrictions for PVID and priority configuration. Check MSC for detailes.

sheBridgePortHostConfigurationProtocol.name: sheBridgePortHostConfigurationProtocol
sheBridgePortHostConfigurationProtocol.description: Used host configuration protocol. Valid values could none(0), useDHCP(1), usePPPoE(2). useDHCPandPPPoE(3).

sheBridgePortCircuitId.name: sheBridgePortCircuitId
sheBridgePortCircuitId.description: Needed for special Options in DHCP or PPPoE. If not configured the default format string from sheBridgeBaseCircuitIdFormat will be used.

sheBridgePortMaxLearnPermitCount.name: sheBridgePortMaxLearnPermitCount
sheBridgePortMaxLearnPermitCount.description: Number of dynamic learned Mac addresses per port. The valid configuration range for dynamic MacAddress learning is 1..2147483647 (0x7fffffff). A value of -1 disable the MacAddress limitation (default for uplink) -> 'No Limit'. A value of 0 disable the dynamic MacAddress learning -> 'Disabled'. Static FdbTable entrys possible. Additional limitations depending on the used CXU or IU type are possible. The default setting for subscriber ports is 16. Note: Syntax modified with R2.8 BFR 2.0.

sheBridgePortMcastGroupPackageList.name: sheBridgePortMcastGroupPackageList
sheBridgePortMcastGroupPackageList.description: That is a list of allowed corresponding indices of the sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageTable for this subscriber. Each index has 16 bit. If no packet is assigned, the string has 0 length.

sheBridgePortMode.name: sheBridgePortMode
sheBridgePortMode.description: Mode of this bridgeport useIpoE, useIpoA, usePPPoA or useAuto. useIpoE is the default setting. This mode will also support PPPoE. useIPoA is only possible for IU_ADSL or IU_SHDSL boards. If no MacAddress is configured in the corresponding MacProfileTable-entry, the NE will autogenerate a own value. In case of usePPPoA, the IU will translate the PPPoA protocol to PPPoE. This configuration is only valid for bridgeports with SubLayerIndex placed on IU_ADSL72 with IFX chipset! A SrcMac-address in sheBridgeIUProfileTable has to be configured for the IU where these port is placed on. The configuration useAuto forces the IU to start a autodetection mode for supporting PPPoA or PPPoE.

sheBridgePortTaggingMode.name: sheBridgePortTaggingMode
sheBridgePortTaggingMode.description: Tagging modes for bridgePort's. This modes are only valid for received frames. Tagging of transmitted frames depends on the bridgeBase-tagging mode and on the vlan-membership. off(0) Untagged frames are tagged with PVID and forwarded. Tagged frames are forwarded unchanged. That is the default value for uplink port's and should not be changed. tagged(1) Frames tagged with the configured VIDs are forwarded unchanged. Untagged frames and frames with unknown VIDs are dropped. Check sheBridgePortReplaceTag value if a received tag should be replaced by PVID. untagged(2) Untagged frames are tagged with PVID and forwarded. Tagged frames are dropped. That is the default value for subscriber port's. NOTE: SHE releases older then R2.5 will only support modes (0) and (1).

sheBridgePortRemoteId.name: sheBridgePortRemoteId
sheBridgePortRemoteId.description: Needed for special Options in DHCP or PPPoE. If not configured the default format string from sheBridgeBaseRemoteIdFormat will be used.

sheBridgePortInnerPVID.name: sheBridgePortInnerPVID
sheBridgePortInnerPVID.description: The Inner PVID of this bridgePort. Taken if no other rule given for VLAN association. The default Value is 1.

sheBridgePortReplaceVlanTag.name: sheBridgePortReplaceVlanTag
sheBridgePortReplaceVlanTag.description: If configured unequal 0, the configured vlan-tag could be received and will be replaced by PVID before forwarding the frame. A zero will disable this feature. Only valid if the Bridgeport is running tagged(1) mode - otherwise must be zero. NOTE: Modified with R2.8. CG based IU's could only support one vlan tag per IU. This configuration is now used for enable/disable the feature on bridgeport-base. For enable, only the configured value from the IU global configuration will be accepted!

sheBridgePortInnerPriority.name: sheBridgePortInnerPriority
sheBridgePortInnerPriority.description: The inner priority of this bridgePort. Taken if no other rule given for VLAN association. The default value is 0.

sheBridgePortIpoaProviderRouterIpAddress.name: sheBridgePortIpoaProviderRouterIpAddress
sheBridgePortIpoaProviderRouterIpAddress.description: The IPoA provider edge router's ip address for this bridgePort. 0.0.0.0 is also a valid setting and force the NE together with a similar entry in sheArpFixedIpAddressTable to retrieve the needed information automatically.

sheBridgePortPppoaSessionId.name: sheBridgePortPppoaSessionId
sheBridgePortPppoaSessionId.description: The session id from a PPP server is for the PPPoA session.

sheBridgePortMcastMaxJoinedGroup.name: sheBridgePortMcastMaxJoinedGroup
sheBridgePortMcastMaxJoinedGroup.description: The maximum number of multicast group's (channels) that this subscriber can join. 0 is a special value and means 'no' access. 255 is a special value and means 'unlimited' access. This configuration is only valid for bridgeports with usage 'subscriber'.

sheBridgePortMcastLeaveMode.name: sheBridgePortMcastLeaveMode
sheBridgePortMcastLeaveMode.description: If normal leave is enabled and the client sends a leave message, the switch sends a query message to the client. When there is no response from the client, it is deleted from the multicast group. If fast leave is enabled, the client is deleted from the multicast group when the switch receives the leave message. New with R2.8: If ehtMode ('explicit host tracking') is enabled, the multicaststream will only be deleted from FDB if all members of this stream has send her leave.

sheBridgePortMcastEHTMode.name: sheBridgePortMcastEHTMode
sheBridgePortMcastEHTMode.description: Enables or disables the 'explicit host tracking' function. If enabled and fastleave-mode is also running, the multicaststream will only be deleted from FDB if all members of this stream has send her leave. Note: Functionality bundled in McastLeaveMode with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortIgmpSubscriberAccessMode.name: sheBridgePortIgmpSubscriberAccessMode
sheBridgePortIgmpSubscriberAccessMode.description: When sheBridgePortIgmpSubscriberAccessMode is set to 0, it means the access mode is IPoE, when set to 1, it means the access mode is PPPoE. Note: Merged parameter for SHE R2.4. R2.8 will not use this configuration and ignore any modification.

sheBridgePortInnerPriorityOption.name: sheBridgePortInnerPriorityOption
sheBridgePortInnerPriorityOption.description: This parameter configures the handling of the inner vlan tag in the doubleTagged scenario. In singleTagged Mode, this parameter definition is not used. If tagged frames are received set the .1p priority bits of this tag. dscp(1) -> according DSCP of IP header (use sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex or sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex) userTag(2) -> no change of the received .1p priority force(3) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortInnerPriority) If a tag is added to an upstream user frame, because untagged frames are received set the .1p priority bits of the added tag. dscp(1) -> according DSCP of IP header (use sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex or sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex) userTag(2) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortInnerPriority, same as force(3)) force(3) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortInnerPriority) New parameters with SHE R2.7 Expanded with R2.8.

sheBridgePortOuterPriorityOption.name: sheBridgePortOuterPriorityOption
sheBridgePortOuterPriorityOption.description: This parameter configures the handling of the outer vlan tag in the doubleTagged and singleTagged scenario. doubleTagged Scenario: If tagged frames are received set the .1p priority bits of the added outer tag. dscp(1) -> according DSCP of IP header (use sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex or sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex) userTag(2) -> copy .1p priority from the assigned inner .1p priority (inner to outer) force(3) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortPriority) If two tag's are added to an upstream user frame, because untagged frames are received set the .1p priority bits of the added outer tag. dscp(1) -> according DSCP of IP header (use sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex or sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex) userTag(2) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortPriority, same as force(3)) force(3) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortPriority) singleTagged Scenario: If tagged frames are received set the .1p priority bits of the tag. dscp(1) -> according DSCP of IP header (use sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex or sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex) userTag(2) -> no change of the received .1p priority force(3) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortPriority) If untagged frames are received set the .1p priority bits of the added tag. dscp(1) -> according DSCP of IP header (use sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex or sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex) userTag(2) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortPriority, same as force(3)) force(3) -> per port configured .1p (sheBridgePortPriority) New parameters with SHE R2.7 Expanded with R2.8.

sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex.name: sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex
sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex.description: This is a pointer to a mapping entry DSCP to .1p. Value 0 (default) means there is no mapping in use or the IU specific assignment via sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex will be used. One of these two pointer's (port specific or IU global) must be valid if sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp(1) and sheBridgePortUsage is subscriber(4). Used if a tag is added to an upstream user frame and sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp to set .1p bits. Used if an upstream user frame is tagged and sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp for .1p range check. NOTE: Convergate based IU's could only support ONE profile for all port's were these mapping should be used!! New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortIpAddressPermitCount.name: sheBridgePortIpAddressPermitCount
sheBridgePortIpAddressPermitCount.description: Maximum number of possible IpAddresses per BridgePort. The assignment could be done via DHCP or fixedIpAddress configuration. Note: There is an additional restriction of possible IpAddresses per UNI port which could never exceeded. Remark this if more then one bridgePort is used on a single UNI port. Additional restrictions could be possible in case of using IpAntispoofing feature. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMatEnabled.name: sheBridgePortMatEnabled
sheBridgePortMatEnabled.description: Enable or disable the MAC address translation feature on bridgePort base. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortIpAsMode.name: sheBridgePortIpAsMode
sheBridgePortIpAsMode.description: This configuration enable/disable the feature IpAntispoofing on bridgePort base. Depending on the used mode, the IU could made the following checks: offIpAs(0) -> IpAs disabled onIpAsNoVlanCheck(1) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured Ip will be forwarded. onIpAsInnerVlanCheck(2) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured couple Ip-InnerTag will be forwarded. onIpAsOuterVlanCheck(3) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured couple Ip-OuterTag will be forwarded. onIpAsBothVlanCheck(4) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured triple Ip-InnerTag-OuterTag will be forwarded. All other frames will be discarded. Bridgeports on IU cards with wintegra chipset will not check any Vlan dependencies, don't care which onIpAsxxx - mode was selected. Only cards with convergate chipset will made the requested differentiation. There is an additional global switch for IpAs available (sheIpAntiSpoofingEnable), which will outvote this configuration if set to 'enable'. The configuration of the valid triple Ip-InnerTag-OuterTag will be done via DHCP or StaticIpAddress configuration. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapProfilePtr.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapProfilePtr
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapProfilePtr.description: Ethertype-VLAN mapping profile pointer to sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapTable (sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapProfIndex). This attribute is optional and the pointer is null when it is not assigned. Note: The bridgeport has to be untagged member of the mapped vlan, assigned via these profile. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortControlUsage.name: sheBridgePortControlUsage
sheBridgePortControlUsage.description: Only the values uplink, cascading, and subcascading could be interchanged. For the feature singleMacMultipleVcc, it is possible to aggregate two or more single VCC's of one physical adsl-link to the vccAggregator. The usage of the single PVC - bridgeports (subscriber) could be set to vccAggregated and the special bridgeport change his usage from vccAggregatorNotUsed to ..Used in that case. It is also possible to set this special bridgeport usage directly and in that case all bridgeports with identical sublayerindex will change her usage to vccAggregated. This configuration has additional restrictions for PVID and priority configuration. Check MSC for detailes. All other changes will be done by NE automatically based on other configurations.

sheBridgePortControlHostConfigurationPro.description: Used host configuration protocol. Valid values could none(0), useDHCP(1), usePPPoE(2).

sheBridgePortControlReplaceVlanTag.name: sheBridgePortControlReplaceVlanTag
sheBridgePortControlReplaceVlanTag.description: Configure a Vlan-Tag which should be replaced by PVID. Check table entry for details. NOTE: Modified with R2.8. CG based IU's could only support one vlan tag per IU. This configuration is now used for enable/disable the feature on bridgeport-base. For enable, only the configured value from the IU global configuration will be accepted!

sheBridgePortControlInnerPriority.name: sheBridgePortControlInnerPriority
sheBridgePortControlInnerPriority.description: The inner priority of this bridgePort. Taken if no other rule given for VLAN association. The default value is the '0'.

sheBridgePortControlMcastMaxJoinedGroup.name: sheBridgePortControlMcastMaxJoinedGroup
sheBridgePortControlMcastMaxJoinedGroup.description: The maximum number of multicast group's that this subscriber can join. 0 is a special value and means 'no' access. 255 is a special value and means 'unlimited' access.

sheBridgePortControlMcastEHTMode.name: sheBridgePortControlMcastEHTMode
sheBridgePortControlMcastEHTMode.description: Enables or disables the 'explicit host tracking' function. NOTE: Functionality bundled in McastLeaveMode with SHE R2.8. Will not longer used by R2.8.

sheBridgePortControlIgmpSubscriberAccess.name: sheBridgePortControlIgmpSubscriberAccessMode
sheBridgePortControlIgmpSubscriberAccess.description: When sheBridgePortIgmpSubscriberAccessMode is set to 0, it means the access mode is IPoE, when set to 1, it means the access mode is PPPoE. Note: Merged parameter for SHE R2.4. R2.8 will not use this configuration and ignore any modification.

sheBridgePortControlMatEnabled.name: sheBridgePortControlMatEnabled
sheBridgePortControlMatEnabled.description: Enable or disable the MAC address translation feature on bridgePort base.

sheBridgePortControlIpAsMode.name: sheBridgePortControlIpAsMode
sheBridgePortControlIpAsMode.description: This configuration enable/disable the feature IpAntispoofing on bridgePort base. Depending on the used mode, the IU could made the following checks: offIpAs(0) -> IpAs disabled onIpAsNoVlanCheck(1) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured Ip will be forwarded. onIpAsInnerVlanCheck(2) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured couple Ip-InnerTag will be forwarded. onIpAsOuterVlanCheck(3) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured couple Ip-OuterTag will be forwarded. onIpAsBothVlanCheck(4) -> IpAs enabled, Only frames with configured triple Ip-InnerTag-OuterTag will be forwarded. All other frames will be discarded. Bridgeports on IU cards with wintegra chipset will not check any Vlan dependencies, don't care which onIpAsxxx - mode was selected. Only cards with convergate chipset will made the requested differentiation. There is an additional global switch for IpAs available (sheIpAntiSpoofingEnable), which will outvote this configuration if set to 'enable'. The configuration of the valid triple Ip-InnerTag-OuterTag will be done via DHCP or StaticIpAddress configuration. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortControlEtypeVlanMapProfileP.name: sheBridgePortControlEtypeVlanMapProfilePtr
sheBridgePortControlEtypeVlanMapProfileP.description: Ethertype-VLAN mapping profile pointer to sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapTable (sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapProfIndex). This attribute is optional and the pointer is null when it is not assigned. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgeIUProfileEntry.description: Needed to configure some IU specific settings. Index should be the entPhysicalIndex of the IU.

sheBridgeIUPPPoASrcMacAddress.name: sheBridgeIUPPPoASrcMacAddress
sheBridgeIUPPPoASrcMacAddress.description: The used Src-MacAddress for this IU if one of her port's is running in PPPoA - mode. The PPPoA session is translated to PPPoE. This configuration should be made before a port could be switched to PPPoA - mode.

sheBridgeIUProfileUsedMATBasis.name: sheBridgeIUProfileUsedMATBasis
sheBridgeIUProfileUsedMATBasis.description: This parameter select the basis for MAT on these IU. This will NOT enable the MAT feature himself, but select the valid configuration for this IU. If useMATperVlan (default) is selected, the settings of sheBridgePortMatEnabled will be ignored. Only settings of sheVlanMatEnable are valid, if the VLAN is used on this IU. If useMATperBridgeport is selected, the handling will be done in an opposite way. If the used basis should be changed, a reboot of the corresponding IU may be needed to come operational. New parameter with R2.8.

sheBridgeIUReplaceVlanTag.name: sheBridgeIUReplaceVlanTag
sheBridgeIUReplaceVlanTag.description: If configured unequal 0, the configured vlan-tag could be received and will be replaced by PVID before forwarding the frame. A zero will disable this feature for this IU. Only valid for IU Bridgeport's which are running tagged(1) mode and only if the NE global tagging mode is singleTag. NOTE: New with R2.8. Configuration was moved from sheBridgePortTable. The corresponding entry in the bridgeport table enable/disable the feature per bridgeport.

sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex.name: sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex
sheBridgeIUDscpPriorityMapIndex.description: This is a pointer to a mapping entry DSCP to .1p. Value 0 (default) means there is no mapping in use or the port specific assignment via sheBridgePortPriorityMapIndex will be used. One of these two pointer's (port specific or IU global) must be valid if sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp(1) and sheBridgePortUsage is subscriber(4). Used if a tag is added to an upstream user frame and sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp to set .1p bits. Used if an upstream user frame is tagged and sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp for .1p range check. NOTE: Convergate based IU's could only support ONE profile for all port's were these mapping should be used!! New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgeIUProfileControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheBridgeIUProfileControlUsedMATBasis.name: sheBridgeIUProfileControlUsedMATBasis
sheBridgeIUProfileControlUsedMATBasis.description: This parameter select the basis for MAT on these IU. This will NOT enable the MAT feature himself, but select the valid configuration for this IU. If useMATperVlan (default) is selected, the settings of sheBridgePortMatEnabled will be ignored. Only settings of sheVlanMatEnable are valid, if the VLAN is used on this IU. If useMATperBridgeport is selected, the handling will be done in an opposite way. If the used basis should be changed, a reboot of the corresponding IU may be needed to come operational. New parameter with R2.8.

sheBridgeIUProfileControlReplaceVlanTag.name: sheBridgeIUProfileControlReplaceVlanTag
sheBridgeIUProfileControlReplaceVlanTag.description: If configured unequal 0, the configured vlan-tag could be received and will be replaced by PVID before forwarding the frame. A zero will disable this feature for this IU. Only valid for IU Bridgeport's which are running tagged(1) mode and only if the NE global tagging mode is singleTag. NOTE: New with R2.8. Configuration was moved from sheBridgePortTable. The corresponding entry in the bridgeport table enable/disable the feature per bridgeport.

sheBridgePortPriorityMapTable.name: sheBridgePortPriorityMapTable
sheBridgePortPriorityMapTable.description: A mapping profile DSCP to .1p. Used if a tag is added to an upstream user frame (when sheBridgePortTaggingMode is untagged or tagged) and sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp. The first table index is the profile number. The second table index and the mapping key is the DSCP field. One default profile with index 1 always exist and can't be deleted but modified.

sheBridgePortPriorityMapEntry.name: sheBridgePortPriorityMapEntry
sheBridgePortPriorityMapEntry.description: A mapping entry DSCP to .1p. Used if a tag is added to an upstream user frame (when sheBridgePortTaggingMode is untagged or tagged) and sheBridgePortPriorityOption is dscp. The first table index is the entry index. The second table index and the mapping key is the DSCP field. One default mapping entry with index 1 always exist and can't be deleted but modified.

sheBridgePortPriorityMapEntryIndex.name: sheBridgePortPriorityMapEntryIndex
sheBridgePortPriorityMapEntryIndex.description: The number of the mapping profile is the first table index.

sheBridgePortPriorityMapDscp.name: sheBridgePortPriorityMapDscp
sheBridgePortPriorityMapDscp.description: Bits 2-7 of TOS field of IP header are called DSCP. DSCP 000000 is the lowest priority (best effort). This is the second table index and the mapping key. Since zero is not allowed as table index, this value is increased by 1 (range is 1..64).

sheBridgePortPriorityMapPrio.name: sheBridgePortPriorityMapPrio
sheBridgePortPriorityMapPrio.description: The .1p priority bits in the VLAN tag is the mapping value.

sheBridgePortPrioMapControlRequest.name: sheBridgePortPrioMapControlRequest
sheBridgePortPrioMapControlRequest.description: One default mapping entry with index 1 always exist and can't be deleted but modified. createBridgePortPrioMapEntry - a complete profile (64 entries) with a default mapping is created deleteBridgePortPrioMapEntry sheBridgePortPrioMapControlIndex - a complete profile (64 entries) is deleted modifyBridgePortPrioMapEntry sheBridgePortPrioMapControlIndex sheBridgePortPrioMapControlDscp sheBridgePortPrioMapControlPrio - a single entry of a profile is modified

sheBridgePortPrioMapControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheBridgePortPrioMapControlDscp.name: sheBridgePortPrioMapControlDscp
sheBridgePortPrioMapControlDscp.description: Bits 2-7 of TOS field of IP header are called DSCP. DSCP 000000 is the lowest priority (best effort). This is the second table index and the mapping key. Since zero is not allowed as table index, this value is increased by 1 (range is 1..64).

sheBridgePortPrioMapControlPrio.name: sheBridgePortPrioMapControlPrio
sheBridgePortPrioMapControlPrio.description: The .1p priority bits in the VLAN tag is the mapping value.

sheBridgePortMCastConfigTable.name: sheBridgePortMCastConfigTable
sheBridgePortMCastConfigTable.description: This table contain all new defined bridgePort specific multicast configurations. New supported with SHE R2.8!

sheBridgePortMCastConfigEntry.name: sheBridgePortMCastConfigEntry
sheBridgePortMCastConfigEntry.description: The MCast configuration settiongs per BridgePort.

sheBridgePortMCastBandwithLimit.name: sheBridgePortMCastBandwithLimit
sheBridgePortMCastBandwithLimit.description: This is the configured multicast bandwith limitation per bridgePort. 0 kbps indicates that no multicast traffic is allowed for the bport. The value 65535 (0xFFFF) is a special value and means unlimited access for this bridgeport (switch off feature AC - admission control - default). New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMCastMinUCBandwithLimit.name: sheBridgePortMCastMinUCBandwithLimit
sheBridgePortMCastMinUCBandwithLimit.description: This is the minimum bandwidth of sustainable unicast traffic for a bridge port. M/C admission control shall include this minimum bandwidth of sustainable unicast traffic within the calculation to reserve a minimum bandwidth for VoD services. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMCastMaxJoinedNonPremiumGro.name: sheBridgePortMCastMaxJoinedNonPremiumGroup
sheBridgePortMCastMaxJoinedNonPremiumGro.description: The maximum number of non-premium multicast group's (channels) that this subscriber can join. 0 is a special value and means 'no' access. 255 is a special value and means 'unlimited' access. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMCastRemainBandwith.name: sheBridgePortMCastRemainBandwith
sheBridgePortMCastRemainBandwith.description: It is the remaining multicast bandwidth of a bridge port. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMCastACStatus.name: sheBridgePortMCastACStatus
sheBridgePortMCastACStatus.description: It indicates the AC (admission control) status of a bridgeport, It can be accept or deny. When it is accepted, it indicates the bridgeport still has enough bandwidth for multicast access. When it is denied, it indicates the bridgeport is short of bandwidth for multicast access. 1 means accept, 0 means deny. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMCastControlIndex.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlIndex
sheBridgePortMCastControlIndex.description: The index of the bridgePort to be configured.

sheBridgePortMCastControlStatus.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlStatus
sheBridgePortMCastControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheBridgePortMCastControlTimer.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlTimer
sheBridgePortMCastControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheBridgePortMCastControlReqResult.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlReqResult
sheBridgePortMCastControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheBridgePortMCastControlTimeStamp.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlTimeStamp
sheBridgePortMCastControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheBridgePortMCastControlBandwithLimit.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlBandwithLimit
sheBridgePortMCastControlBandwithLimit.description: This is the configured multicast bandwith limitation per bridgePort. 0 kbps indicates that no multicast traffic is allowed for the bport. The value 655353 (0xFFFF) is a special value and means unlimited access for this bridgeport (switch off feature AC - admission control). New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMCastControlMinUCBandwithLi.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlMinUCBandwithLimit
sheBridgePortMCastControlMinUCBandwithLi.description: This is the minimum bandwidth of sustainable unicast traffic for a bridge port. M/C admission control shall include this minimum bandwidth of sustainable unicast traffic within the calculation to reserve a minimum bandwidth for VoD services. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortMCastControlMaxJoinedNonPre.name: sheBridgePortMCastControlMaxJoinedNonPremiumGroup
sheBridgePortMCastControlMaxJoinedNonPre.description: The maximum number of non-premium multicast group's that this subscriber can join. 0 is a special value and means 'no' access. 255 is a special value and means 'unlimited' access. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapTable.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapTable
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapTable.description: This table is used with SHE R2.8. Ethertype-VLAN mapping profiles. Index is the profile index.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapEntry.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapEntry
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapEntry.description: This table is used with SHE R2.8. Ethertype-VLAN mapping profiles. Index is the profile index.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapEthertype.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapEthertype
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapEthertype.description: That is a list of possible 16bit protocol type field's of the ethernet frames. The octet string is a list of two octet entries each identifying an ethertyp value The least significant byte is the second octet. The octet string has a variable length of up to 16 octets (max. 8 ethertypes in the list). examples: 0x0800 IP Internet Protocol (IPv4) 0x0806 Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) 0x8100 VLAN Tag (VLAN) 0x8863 PPPoE Discovery 0x8864 PPPoE Session The VlanMapping is applied to upstream frames matching this Ethertype's. Other frames are forwarded unchanged.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapVlanId.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapVlanId
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapVlanId.description: A VLAN identifier mapped to the Ethertype's.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapPriority.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapPriority
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapPriority.description: The priority part of the VLAN tag mapped to the Ethertype's.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapControlReqResul.description: The result of the last user command.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapControlTimeStam.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlProfIndex.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlProfIndex
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlProfIndex.description: The Ethertype-VLAN mapping profile index (first index).

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlEthertype.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlEthertype
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlEthertype.description: That is a list of possible 16bit protocol type field's of the ethernet frames. The octet string is a list of two octet entries each identifying an ethertyp value. The least significant byte is the second octet. The octet string has a variable length of up to 16 octets (max. 8 ethertypes in the list). examples: 0x0800 IP Internet Protocol (IPv4) 0x0806 Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) 0x8100 VLAN Tag (VLAN) 0x8863 PPPoE Discovery 0x8864 PPPoE Session The VlanMapping is applied to upstream frames matching this Ethertype's. Other frames are forwarded unchanged.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlVlanId.description: A VLAN identifier mapped to the Ethertype's.

sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlPriority.name: sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlPriority
sheBridgePortEtypeVlanMapCtrlPriority.description: The priority part of the VLAN tag mapped to the Ethertype's.

sheBridgeExtResidentialTable.name: sheBridgeExtResidentialTable
sheBridgeExtResidentialTable.description: Only supported by SHE hiX5608 !! Table index is the ifIndex of uplink or trunk interfaces.

sheBridgeExtResidentialControlRequest.name: sheBridgeExtResidentialControlRequest
sheBridgeExtResidentialControlRequest.description: New with R2.8 - Only supported by SHE hiX5608 !!: setExtResidentialMode (990): sheBridgeExtResidentialControlPortIndex sheBridgeExtResidentialControlMode ->sheBridgeExtResidentialModeModified

sheBridgeExtResidentialControlStatus.name: sheBridgeExtResidentialControlStatus
sheBridgeExtResidentialControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheBridgeExtResidentialControlTimer.name: sheBridgeExtResidentialControlTimer
sheBridgeExtResidentialControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheBridgeExtResidentialControlReqResult.name: sheBridgeExtResidentialControlReqResult
sheBridgeExtResidentialControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheBridgeExtResidentialControlTimeStamp.name: sheBridgeExtResidentialControlTimeStamp
sheBridgeExtResidentialControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheVlanEntry.name: sheVlanEntry
sheVlanEntry.description: One entry for every existing vlan in the system.

sheVlanName.name: sheVlanName
sheVlanName.description: A descriptional name for that vlan. Spaces and other special characters (: o) are not allowed!!

sheVlanStatus.name: sheVlanStatus
sheVlanStatus.description: static, in future gvrp values: static(1), dynamic(2)

sheVlanEgressPorts.name: sheVlanEgressPorts
sheVlanEgressPorts.description: Portlist for all member of this VLAN, they will send tagged or untagged frames. The octet string is a list of pairs of octets each identify an sheBridgePortIndex. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheVlanUnTaggedPorts.name: sheVlanUnTaggedPorts
sheVlanUnTaggedPorts.description: Portlist for members of this Vlan they will send only untagged frames. The octet string is a list of pairs of octets each identify an sheBridgePortIndex. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheVlanFdbId.name: sheVlanFdbId
sheVlanFdbId.description: First index of the used Filtering Table. The value would be in current implementation identical to the VlanIndex.

sheVlanCreationTime.name: sheVlanCreationTime
sheVlanCreationTime.description: Only useful in case of gvrp.

sheVlanMulticastPermission.name: sheVlanMulticastPermission
sheVlanMulticastPermission.description: Permission to transmit multicast-traffic. If a vlan has this permission, it could transmit multicast-traffic or igmp-request's. Transmission of non MC traffic is always possible. NOTE: SHE R2.6 will not longer support this configuration. A McastPermission per Vlan is not needed anymore and each existing Vlan is able to transport mcast traffic.

sheVlanDhcpProviderIndex.name: sheVlanDhcpProviderIndex
sheVlanDhcpProviderIndex.description: Points to the Vlan associated Dhcp-Provider entry in the DhcpProvider-Table. Default 0 -> DHCP Relay for this Vlan is deactivated. This value should also be 0 if this vlan will be used as a DHCP or PPPoE provider vlan (sheDhcpVlanId).

sheVlanDefaultGateway.name: sheVlanDefaultGateway
sheVlanDefaultGateway.description: Only needed if this VLAN is used as subscriber Vlan (PVID for a bridgeport) and the corresponding bridgeport use IpoA mode. Otherwise don't care. NOTE: Configuration not longer needed with R2.8. Funcionality replaced by bridgePort configuration of sheBridgePortIpoaProviderRouterIpAddress.

sheVlanPPPoEProviderIndex.name: sheVlanPPPoEProviderIndex
sheVlanPPPoEProviderIndex.description: Points to the Vlan associated PPPoE-Provider entry in the DhcpProvider-Table. Default 0 -> PPPoE Relay for this Vlan is deactivated. This value should also be 0 if this vlan will be used as a PPPoE or DHCP provider vlan (sheDhcpVlanId).

sheVlanMgmtVlan.name: sheVlanMgmtVlan
sheVlanMgmtVlan.description: Specify the VLAN that doesn't allows for subscriber ports to be joined.

sheVlanServiceTagOnly.name: sheVlanServiceTagOnly
sheVlanServiceTagOnly.description: A customer tag is not expected for the VLAN in the double tagging mode. Note: This configuration is not longer supported with SHE R2.6.

sheVlanAgeingTime.name: sheVlanAgeingTime
sheVlanAgeingTime.description: MAC aging time for the VLAN. If the value is '0', it means that aging time for the VLAN follows global agiang time which is defined as 'sheFdbBaseAgeingTime'.

sheVlanRoutingMode.name: sheVlanRoutingMode
sheVlanRoutingMode.description: Generally, the default routing mode is residential; all packets cannot be forwarded between subscribers on the same VLAN. But if this mode is true, the communication between subscribers becomes available. (Default: false).

sheVlanTunnelingL2Protocol.name: sheVlanTunnelingL2Protocol
sheVlanTunnelingL2Protocol.description: If L2VPN is supported, all L2 protocol packets should be set as flood or drop. The value of this attribute is true, all L2 protocol packets is flooded to customers networks. (Default: false). Note: This configuration is not longer supported with SHE R2.8.

sheVlanServiceType.name: sheVlanServiceType
sheVlanServiceType.description: Define a tagging/stripping method in NE DT mode. 1 - It is a DoubleTagging mode for a VLAN. It strips both C-tag and S-tag in DSLAM. 2 - It is a VlanStacking mode for a VLAN. It strips an S-tag in DSLAM.

sheVlanDlfFlood.name: sheVlanDlfFlood
sheVlanDlfFlood.description: If it is enabled, DLF packets should be flooded to the line card which is set to sheVlanDlfFloodCard regardless of BridgeBase DLF state. In case it is disabled, handling of DLF packets comply with BridgeBase DLF state. The maxium number of vlan which is set to enable is 50. (Default:false)

sheVlanDlfFloodCard.name: sheVlanDlfFloodCard
sheVlanDlfFloodCard.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the line card where to flood DLF packets from uplink

sheVlanCCMode.name: sheVlanCCMode
sheVlanCCMode.description: This parameter describes the handling of broadcast (bc), unknown multicast (umc) and unknown unicast (uuc) traffic for this vlan. If cross connect mode is True all these packets are flooded in the VLAN otherwise they are droped. Supported by R2.5.1 and higher.

sheVlanRouted.name: sheVlanRouted
sheVlanRouted.description: Configure the handling of ARP request's in the NE for this vlan. Valid values: switching - A ARP request from Network side will be answered with CPE mac address. routing - A ARP request from Network side will be answered with DSLAM mac address. Supported by R2.5.1 and higher.

sheVlanMcastFlood.name: sheVlanMcastFlood
sheVlanMcastFlood.description: If it is enabled, all mcast packets should be flooded in this vlan.

sheVlanMatEnable.name: sheVlanMatEnable
sheVlanMatEnable.description: Enable or disable the MAC address translation feature on Vlan base. The feature will use the ingress vlan to decide if the mac address of a member bridgePort should be translated. For bridgePorts they receive only untagged frames, the feature could be enabled via the PVID vlan.

sheVlanSubportServiceName.name: sheVlanSubportServiceName
sheVlanSubportServiceName.description: The format identifier %R in sheBridgeBaseCircuitIdFormat, sheBridgePortCircuitId, sheBridgeBaseRemoteIdFormat and sheBridgePortRemoteId is replaced by this string. If the string is empty, %R is replaced by the VLAN ID. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheVlanUplinkTranslationVlan.name: sheVlanUplinkTranslationVlan
sheVlanUplinkTranslationVlan.description: This parameter enable a bidirectional vlanTranslation on Uplink side. The Vlan, identified by sheVlanIndex of this table-entry (subscriber side) will be translated to the vlan configured with this parameter. 0 - disabled -> is the default value and will disable the vlan translation. 65535 - usedAsTranslationVlan -> this vlan is already in use as an Translation-Vlan and could not be translated This configuration will only be valid for protocolframes, which are routed via hostprocessor. SharedVlanLearning has to be enabled (bridgeBase parameter)! For translation of usertraffic, additional rules has to be configured!

A McastPermission per Vlan is not needed anymore and each existing Vlan is able to transport mcast traffic.

sheVlanControlPPPoEProviderIndex.description: Points to the Vlan associated PPPoE-Provider entry in the DhcpProvider-Table. Default 0 -> PPPoE Relay for this Vlan is deactivated.

sheVlanControlMgmtVlan.name: sheVlanControlMgmtVlan
sheVlanControlMgmtVlan.description: Specify the VLAN that doesn't allow subscribers to join.

sheVlanControlServiceTagOnly.name: sheVlanControlServiceTagOnly
sheVlanControlServiceTagOnly.description: A customer tag is not expected for the VLAN in the double tagging mode. Note: This configuration is not longer supported with SHE R2.6.

sheVlanControlAgeingTime.name: sheVlanControlAgeingTime
sheVlanControlAgeingTime.description: MAC aging time for the VLAN. If the value is '0', it means that aging time for the VLAN follows global agiang time which is defined as 'sheFdbBaseAgeingTime'.

sheVlanControlRoutingMode.name: sheVlanControlRoutingMode
sheVlanControlRoutingMode.description: Generally, the default routing mode is residential; all packets cannot be forwarded between subscribers on the same VLAN. But if this mode is true, the communication between subscribers becomes available. (Default: false).

sheVlanControlServiceType.name: sheVlanControlServiceType
sheVlanControlServiceType.description: Set a tagging/stripping method in NE DT mode.

sheVlanControlDlfFlood.description: If it is enabled, DLF packets should be flooded to the line card which is set to sheVlanDlfFloodCard regardless of BridgeBase DLF state. In case it is disabled, handling of DLF packets comply with BridgeBase DLF state. The maxium number of vlan which is set to enable is 50. (Default:false)

The feature will use the ingress vlan to decide if the mac address of a member bridgePort should be translated. For bridgePorts they receive only untagged frames, the feature could be enabled via the PVID vlan.

sheVlanPortsModified.name: sheVlanPortsModified
sheVlanPortsModified.description: A vlan portlist was modified by command setVlanPorts.

sheVlanMgmtVlanChanged.name: sheVlanMgmtVlanChanged
sheVlanMgmtVlanChanged.description: A vlan is assigned as Mgmt-Vlan.

sheVlanServiceTagOnlyChanged.name: sheVlanServiceTagOnlyChanged
sheVlanServiceTagOnlyChanged.description: A customer tagging policy for a VLAN has been changed.

sheVlanAgeingTimeChanged.name: sheVlanAgeingTimeChanged
sheVlanAgeingTimeChanged.description: MAC ageing time for a VLAN has been changed.

sheVlanRoutingModeChanged.name: sheVlanRoutingModeChanged
sheVlanRoutingModeChanged.description: Local switching for a VLAN has been changed.

sheVlanTunnelingL2ProtocolChanged.name: sheVlanTunnelingL2ProtocolChanged
sheVlanTunnelingL2ProtocolChanged.description: L2 protocol for a VLAN has been changed.

sheVlanServiceTypeChanged.name: sheVlanServiceTypeChanged
sheVlanServiceTypeChanged.description: Vlan service type for a VLAN has been changed.

sheVlanDlfFloodChanged.name: sheVlanDlfFloodChanged
sheVlanDlfFloodChanged.description: A policy for handling Dlf packets has been changed.

sheVlanPortslistModified.description: Configuration trap after changing the current vlan portlist's by using the commands addVlanPorts or deleteVlanPorts.

sheVlanMatEnableChanged.name: sheVlanMatEnableChanged
sheVlanMatEnableChanged.description: MAC address translation feature on Vlan base changed.

genericRule-Type the set of used pattern matches and action are not fixed. The NE has to parse the complete control-group and the managment system must send the complete control-group, but only pattern with a match-value unequal ignore will be evaluated. Be careful!! genericAdminRule(51) sheRuleControlType= 51 In case of using the genericAdminRule-Type the set of used pattern matches and action are not fixed. The NE has to parse the complete control-group and the managment system must send the complete control-group, but only pattern with a match-value unequal ignore will be evaluated. Be careful!! The only difference to rule-type 50, genericRule, is, that the AdminRule will complete handled by CXU-Software, without support of switching fabric!!

sheRuleGenericMatchAction.name: sheRuleGenericMatchAction
sheRuleGenericMatchAction.description: Handle packet as follows if rule match. - deny(0) Drops matching packets. Action parameter: none - allow(1) Permits matching packets. Action parameter: none - meter(2) Maps an rate limiting profile. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericMatchActionMeterIndex - redirect(3) Redirects matching packets to given bridge port (uplink interface). Action parameter: sheRuleGenericMatchActionRedirPort - mirror(4) Copies matching packets to mirror monitor port. Action parameter: none - setDscp(5) Sets DSCP value in matching packets. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericMatchActionDscp - setPriority(6) Schedules matching frames (queue mapping) according given priority value. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericMatchActionSetPrio - changeTagPriority(7) Changes .1p priority value in VLAN tag. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericMatchActionSetTagPrio - changeTagPriorityWithTos(8) Copies IP Precedence Bits of TOS field into .1p priority of VLAN tag. Action parameter: none - setIpPrecedence(9) Sets IP Precedence bits in TOS field. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericMatchActionIpPrecedence - changeTosWithTagPrio(10) Action parameter: none - rateLimit(11) Applies rate limiting for matching packets. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericMatchActionRate - changeVlanId(12) Changes Vlan-ID in VLAN-Tag of matching frames. Action parameter: sheRuleActionVlan - copyToCpu(13) Copies matching frames to CPU port. Action parameter: none - count(14) Initiates counting of matching packets. The NE supports only a limited number of counters at the same time and may reject this rule if the number of timers is exceeded. - untag (15) untag the frame

sheRuleGenericNoMatchAction.name: sheRuleGenericNoMatchAction
sheRuleGenericNoMatchAction.description: Handle packet as follows if rule not match. - deny(0) Drops matching packets. Action parameter: none - allow(1) Permits matching packets. Action parameter: none - meter(2) Maps an rate limiting profile. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericNoMatchActionMeterIndex - redirect(3) Redirects matching packets to given bridge port (uplink interface). Action parameter: sheRuleGenericNoMatchActionRedirPort - mirror(4) Copies matching packets to mirror monitor port. Action parameter: none - setDscp(5) Sets DSCP value in matching packets. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericNoMatchActionDscp - setPriority(6) Schedules matching frames (queue mapping) according given priority value. Action parameter: sheRuleActionSetPrio - changeTagPriority(7) Changes .1p priority value in VLAN tag. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericNoMatchActionSetTagPrio - changeTagPriorityWithTos(8) Copies IP Precedence Bits of TOS field into .1p priority of VLAN tag. Action parameter: none - setIpPrecedence(9) Sets IP Precedence bits in TOS field. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericNoMatchActionIpPrecedence - changeTosWithTagPrio(10) Action parameter: none - rateLimit(11) Applies rate limiting for matching packets. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericNoMatchActionRate - changeVlanId(12) Changes Vlan-ID in VLAN-Tag of matching frames. Action parameter: sheRuleGenericNoMatchActionVlan - copyToCpu(13) Copies matching frames to CPU port. Action parameter: none - count(14) Initiates counting of matching packets. The NE supports only a limited number of counters at the same time and may reject this rule if the number of timers is exceeded. - untag (15) untag the frame

sheFdbTable.name: sheFdbTable
sheFdbTable.description: The forwarding data base table. New with R2.8 maintenance: This release introduces a new ControlRequest command for refresh of this table. Without calling this command, the table content will be static and not longer automatically updated. The refresh command could be used together with the vlanIndex, which is the first table index here. If a valid vlanIndex value was used, only the tableEntries with this vlanIndex as first key will be refreshed. If the vlanIndex is 0 or unknown the full table will be refreshed.

sheFdbStatus.name: sheFdbStatus
