sheLagGroupMacAddress.name: sheLagGroupMacAddress
sheLagGroupMacAddress.description: A 6-octet read-only value carrying the individual MAC address assigned to the Aggregator.

sheLagGroupActorSystemPriority.name: sheLagGroupActorSystemPriority
sheLagGroupActorSystemPriority.description: A 2-octet value indicating the priority value associated with the Actor's System ID.

sheLagGroupActorSystemId.name: sheLagGroupActorSystemId
sheLagGroupActorSystemId.description: A 6-octet read-write MAC address value used as a unique identifier for the System that contains this Aggregator.

sheLagGroupAggregateOrIndividual.name: sheLagGroupAggregateOrIndividual
sheLagGroupAggregateOrIndividual.description: A read-only Boolean value indicating whether the Aggregator represents an Aggregate ('TRUE') or an Individual link ('FALSE').

sheLagGroupActorAdminKey.name: sheLagGroupActorAdminKey
sheLagGroupActorAdminKey.description: The current administrative value of the Key for the Aggregator. The administrative Key value may differ from the operational Key value for the reasons discussed in 43.6.2. The meaning of particular Key values is of local significance.

sheLagGroupActorOperKey.name: sheLagGroupActorOperKey
sheLagGroupActorOperKey.description: The current operational value of the Key for the Aggregator. The administrative Key value may differ from the operational Key value for the reasons discussed in 43.6.2. This is a 16-bit, read-only value. The meaning of particular Key values is of local significance.

sheLagGroupPartnerSystemId.name: sheLagGroupPartnerSystemId
sheLagGroupPartnerSystemId.description: A 6-octet read-only MAC address value consisting of the unique identifier for the current protocol Partner of this Aggregator. A value of zero indicates that there is no known Partner. If the aggregation is manually configured, this System ID value will be a value assigned by the local System.

sheLagGroupPartnerSystemPriority.name: sheLagGroupPartnerSystemPriority
sheLagGroupPartnerSystemPriority.description: A 2-octet read-only value that indicates the priority value associated with the Partner's System ID. If the aggregation is manually configured, this System Priority value will be a value assigned by the local System.

sheLagGroupPartnerOperKey.name: sheLagGroupPartnerOperKey
sheLagGroupPartnerOperKey.description: The current operational value of the Key for the Aggregator's current protocol Partner. This is a 16-bit, read-only value. If the aggregation is manually configured, this Key value will be a value assigned by the local System.

sheLagGroupCollectorMaxDelay.name: sheLagGroupCollectorMaxDelay
sheLagGroupCollectorMaxDelay.description: The value of this 16-bit attribute defines the maximum delay, in tens of microseconds, that may be imposed by the Frame Collector between receiving a frame from an Aggregator Parser and either delivering the frame to its MAC Client or discarding the frame (see 43.2.3.1.1). Note: R2.8 will not longer accept any modification of this parameter and use always NE internal value.

sheLagGroupLacpActivity.name: sheLagGroupLacpActivity
sheLagGroupLacpActivity.description: This attribute will enable or disable LACP-Activity for this Lag-Group.

sheLagGroupMethod.name: sheLagGroupMethod
sheLagGroupMethod.description: Possible values: srcmac(1), dstmac(2), xormac(3), srcip(4), dstip(5), xorip(6)

sheLagGroupPortList.name: sheLagGroupPortList
sheLagGroupPortList.description: Portlist for all member's of this LAG. The octet string is a list of pairs of octets each identify an sheBridgePortIndex. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheLagGroupEntPhysicalIndex.name: sheLagGroupEntPhysicalIndex
sheLagGroupEntPhysicalIndex.description: This attribute describes the entPhysicalIndex of the card, where this LAG group is placed. Only LagPorts with identical entPhysicalIndex for the card could be added to a group. This information is given via: sheLagGroupPortList -> sheLagPortEntry -> sheBridgePortIndex -> sheSublayerIndex -> ifIndex -> shePhysPortEntPhysicalIndex

sheLagPortTable.name: sheLagPortTable
sheLagPortTable.description: A table that contains Link Aggregation Control configuration information about every Aggregation Port associated with this device. A row appears in this table for each physical port. For she, this table will contain allways 4 entrys.

sheLagPortEntry.name: sheLagPortEntry
sheLagPortEntry.description: A list of Link Aggregation Control configuration parameters for each Aggregation Port on this device.

sheLagPortActorSystemPriority.name: sheLagPortActorSystemPriority
sheLagPortActorSystemPriority.description: A 2-octet value used to define the priority value associated with the Actor's System ID.

sheLagPortActorSystemId.name: sheLagPortActorSystemId
sheLagPortActorSystemId.description: A 6-octet read-only MAC address value that defines the value of the System ID for the System that contains this Aggregation Port.

sheLagPortActorAdminKey.name: sheLagPortActorAdminKey
sheLagPortActorAdminKey.description: The current administrative value of the Key for the Aggregation Port. This is a 16-bit, read-write value. The meaning of particular Key values is of local significance.

sheLagPortActorOperKey.name: sheLagPortActorOperKey
sheLagPortActorOperKey.description: The current operational value of the Key for the Aggregation Port. This is a 16-bit, read-only value. The meaning of particular Key values is of local significance.

sheLagPortPartnerAdminSystemPriority.name: sheLagPortPartnerAdminSystemPriority
sheLagPortPartnerAdminSystemPriority.description: A 2-octet value used to define the administrative value of priority associated with the Partner's System ID. The assigned value is used, along with the value of PortPartnerAdminSystemID, PortPartnerAdminKey, PortPartnerAdminPort, and PortPartnerAdminPortPriority, in order to achieve manually configured aggregation.

sheLagPortPartnerOperSystemPriority.name: sheLagPortPartnerOperSystemPriority
sheLagPortPartnerOperSystemPriority.description: A 2-octet read-only value indicating the operational value of priority associated with the Partner's System ID. The value of this attribute may contain the manually configured value carried in PortPartnerAdminSystemPriority if there is no protocol Partner.

sheLagPortPartnerAdminSystemId.name: sheLagPortPartnerAdminSystemId
sheLagPortPartnerAdminSystemId.description: A 6-octet MACAddress value representing the administrative value of the Aggregation Port's protocol Partner's System ID. The assigned value is used, along with the value of PortPartnerAdminSystemPriority, PortPartnerAdminKey, PortPartnerAdminPort, and PortPartnerAdminPortPriority, in order to achieve manually configured aggregation.

sheLagPortPartnerOperSystemId.name: sheLagPortPartnerOperSystemId
sheLagPortPartnerOperSystemId.description: A 6-octet read-only MACAddress value representing the current value of the Aggregation Port's protocol Partner's System ID. A value of zero indicates that there is no known protocol Partner. The value of this attribute may contain the manually configured value carried in PortPartnerAdminSystemID if there is no protocol Partner.

sheLagPortPartnerAdminKey.name: sheLagPortPartnerAdminKey
sheLagPortPartnerAdminKey.description: The current administrative value of the Key for the protocol Partner. This is a 16-bit, read-write value. The assigned value is used, along with the value of PortPartnerAdminSystemPriority, PortPartnerAdminSystemID, PortPartnerAdminPort, and PortPartnerAdminPortPriority, in order to achieve manually configured aggregation.

sheLagPortPartnerOperKey.name: sheLagPortPartnerOperKey
sheLagPortPartnerOperKey.description: The current operational value of the Key for the protocol Partner. The value of this attribute may contain the manually configured value carried in PortPartnerAdminKey if there is no protocol Partner. This is a 16-bit, read-only value.

sheLagPortSelectedAggId.name: sheLagPortSelectedAggId
sheLagPortSelectedAggId.description: The identifier value of the Aggregator that this Aggregation Port has currently selected. Zero indicates that the Aggregation Port has not selected an Aggregator, either because it is in the process of detaching from an Aggregator or because there is no suitable Aggregator available for it to select. This value is read-only.

sheLagPortAttachedAggId.name: sheLagPortAttachedAggId
sheLagPortAttachedAggId.description: The identifier value of the Aggregator that this Aggregation Port is currently attached to. Zero indicates that the Aggregation Port is not currently attached to an Aggregator. This value is read-only.

sheLagPortActorPort.name: sheLagPortActorPort
sheLagPortActorPort.description: The port number locally assigned to the Aggregation Port. The port number is communicated in LACPDUs as the Actor_Port. This value is read-only.

sheLagPortActorPortPriority.name: sheLagPortActorPortPriority
sheLagPortActorPortPriority.description: The priority value assigned to this Aggregation Port. This is a 2-octet value.

sheLagPortPartnerAdminPort.name: sheLagPortPartnerAdminPort
sheLagPortPartnerAdminPort.description: The current administrative value of the port number for the protocol Partner. This is a 16-bit value. The assigned value is used, along with the value of PortPartnerAdminSystemPriority,PortPartnerAdminSystemID, PartnerAdminKey, and PortPartnerAdminPortPriority, in order to achieve manually configured aggregation.

sheLagPortPartnerOperPort.name: sheLagPortPartnerOperPort
sheLagPortPartnerOperPort.description: The operational port number assigned to this Aggregation Port by the Aggregation Port's protocol Partner. The value of this attribute may contain the manually configured value carried in aAggPortPartnerAdminPort if there is no protocol Partner. This 16-bit value is read-only.

sheLagPortPartnerAdminPortPriority.name: sheLagPortPartnerAdminPortPriority
sheLagPortPartnerAdminPortPriority.description: The current administrative value of the port priority for the protocol Partner. This is a 16-bit value. The assigned value is used, along with the value of PortPartnerAdminSystemPriority, PortPartnerAdminSystemID, PortPartnerAdminKey, and PortPartnerAdminPort, in order to achieve manually configured aggregation.

sheLagPortPartnerOperPortPriority.name: sheLagPortPartnerOperPortPriority
sheLagPortPartnerOperPortPriority.description: The priority value assigned to this Aggregation Port by the Partner. The value of this attribute may contain the manually configured value carried in PortPartnerAdminPortPriority if there is no.

sheLagPortActorAdminState.name: sheLagPortActorAdminState
sheLagPortActorAdminState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the administrative values of Actor_State (43.4.2) as transmitted by the Actor in LACPDUs. The first bit of string corresponds to bit 7 (Expired). If TRUE (encoded as a 1), this flag indicates that the Actor's receive machine is in the EXPIRED state The second of string bit corresponds to bit 6 (Defaulted). If TRUE (encoded as a 1), this flag indicates that the Actor's receive machine is using Defaulted operational Partner information, administratively configured for the Partner. The third of string bit corresponds to bit 5 (Distributing). FALSE (encoded as a 0) means distribution of outgoing frames on this link is definitely disabled. The fourth of string bit corresponds to bit 4(Collecting). TRUE (encoded as a 1) means collection of incoming frames on this link is definitely enabled. The fifth of string bit corresponds to bit 3 (Synchronization). If FALSE (encoded as a 0), then this link is currently OUT_OF_SYNC, i.e., it is not in the right Aggregation. The sixth of string bit corresponds to bit 2 (Aggregation). If FALSE (encoded as a 0), the link is considered to be Individual, i.e., this link can be operated only as an individual link. The seventh of string bit corresponds to bit 1 (LACP_Timeout). Short Timeout is encoded as a 1; Long Timeout is encoded as a 0. The eighth of string bit corresponds to bit 0 of Actor_State (LACP_Activity). Active LACP is encoded as a 1; Passive LACP is encoded as a 0. The values of LACP_Activity,LACP_Timeout and Aggregation allow administrative control and could be set by controlgroup.

sheLagPortActorOperState.name: sheLagPortActorOperState
sheLagPortActorOperState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current operational values of Actor_State as transmitted by the Actor in LACPDUs.

sheLagPortPartnerAdminState.name: sheLagPortPartnerAdminState
sheLagPortPartnerAdminState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current administrative value of Actor_State for the protocol Partner. The assigned value is used in order to achieve manually configured aggregation.

sheLagPortPartnerOperState.name: sheLagPortPartnerOperState
sheLagPortPartnerOperState.description: A string of 8 bits, corresponding to the current values of Actor_State in the most recently received LACPDU transmitted by the protocol Partner. In the absence of an active protocol Partner, this value may reflect the manually configured value PortPartnerAdminState. This attribute value is read-only.

sheLagPortAggregateOrIndividual.name: sheLagPortAggregateOrIndividual
sheLagPortAggregateOrIndividual.description: A read-only Boolean value indicating whether the Aggregation Port is able to Aggregate ('TRUE') or is only able to operate as an Individual link ('FALSE').

sheLagPortLacpAvailability.name: sheLagPortLacpAvailability
sheLagPortLacpAvailability.description: This attribute indicates, if this port is available for lacp or not.

sheLagControlRequest.name: sheLagControlRequest
sheLagControlRequest.description: modifyLagGroupEntry: sheLagControlIndex sheLagControlGroupActorSystemPriority sheLagControlGroupActorAdminKey sheLagControlGroupCollectorMaxDelay sheLagControlGroupLacpActivity sheLagControlGroupMethod modifyLagPortEntry: sheLagControlIndex sheLagControlPortActorAdminKey sheLagControlPortActorPortPriority sheLagControlPortActorAdminState sheLagControlPortLacpAvailability assignBridgePortToLag: sheLagControlIndex sheLagControlGroupPortList unassignBridgePortFromLag: sheLagControlIndex sheLagControlGroupPortList

sheLagControlIndex.name: sheLagControlIndex
sheLagControlIndex.description: The index of the table entry to be configured.

sheLagControlStatus.name: sheLagControlStatus
sheLagControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheLagControlTimer.name: sheLagControlTimer
sheLagControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheLagControlReqResult.name: sheLagControlReqResult
sheLagControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheLagControlTimeStamp.name: sheLagControlTimeStamp
sheLagControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheLagControlGroupCollectorMaxDelay.name: sheLagControlGroupCollectorMaxDelay
sheLagControlGroupCollectorMaxDelay.description: Look at group-table description... Note: R2.8 will not longer use any modification of this parameter and use always NE internal value. A modification will be ignored.

sheLagControlPortActorAdminState.name: sheLagControlPortActorAdminState
sheLagControlPortActorAdminState.description: Look at port-table description...Only bit 0, 1 and 2 could be configured.

sheDhcpRelayAdminState.name: sheDhcpRelayAdminState
sheDhcpRelayAdminState.description: Globaly enable/disable of Dhcp/PPPoE agent. Telegram handling for DHCP and PPPoE relay: valid telegrams are handled, invalid telegrams are dropped snoop: valid telegrams are forwarded, invalid telegrams are dropped bridge: valid telegrams are forwarded, invalid telegrams are forwarded (currently NO support) handling explanation: dhcpPppoeRelayRelay -> dhcp and Pppoe use mode relay dhcpPppoeRelaySnoop -> dhcp use mode relay and Pppoe use mode snoop valid values: up(1), -> releases >= R2.5 run now dhcpPppoeRelayRelay mode down(2), -> releases >= R2.5 run now dhcpPppoeSnoopSnoop mode dhcpPppoeRelayRelay(4), dhcpPppoeRelaySnoop(5), dhcpPppoeRelayBridge(6), (currently NO support) dhcpPppoeSnoopRelay(7), dhcpPppoeSnoopSnoop(8), dhcpPppoeSnoopBridge(9), (currently NO support) dhcpPppoeBridgeRelay(10),(currently NO support) dhcpPppoeBridgeSnoop(11),(currently NO support) dhcpPppoeBridgeBridge(12)(currently NO support) NOTE: Only release R2.5 and higher can accept new value's 4..12 depending on the state of implementation in NE.

sheDhcpRelayRemoteId.name: sheDhcpRelayRemoteId
sheDhcpRelayRemoteId.description: Per default it is the Mac-Address of the DSLAM (length is 6) to be identified for Option 82. Could be set by operator. Moved to sheBridgePortTable and sheBridgeBase. (obsolete)

sheDhcpUseInnerTagForProtocols.name: sheDhcpUseInnerTagForProtocols
sheDhcpUseInnerTagForProtocols.description: This configuration is only valid in double tagged mode. If enabled (true), the protocol machines for all DHCP providers will use the informations from inner tag of a received frame for evaluation, handling and forwarding. Per default always the outer tag will used. New with SHE R.8.

shePppoeUseInnerTagForProtocols.name: shePppoeUseInnerTagForProtocols
shePppoeUseInnerTagForProtocols.description: This configuration is only valid in double tagged mode. If enabled (true), the protocol machines for all PPPoE providers will use the informations from inner tag of a received frame for evaluation, handling and forwarding. Per default always the outer tag will used. New with SHE R.8.

sheDhcpStationMoveEnabled.name: sheDhcpStationMoveEnabled
sheDhcpStationMoveEnabled.description: This parameter configure the feature 'station move' for service issues. If enabled, the NE will instantly release all DHCP session informations and possibly learned mac addresses for a certain subscriber line if a 'link down' event for this line was detected. If disabled, all release actions will be done according to FDB aging time and DHCP lease time configuration. New with R2.8.

sheDhcpProviderEntry.name: sheDhcpProviderEntry
sheDhcpProviderEntry.description: One entry for each known dhcp or pppoe provider (depends on the option settings).

sheDhcpProviderName.name: sheDhcpProviderName
sheDhcpProviderName.description: Descriptional name. Spaces and other special characters (: o) are not allowed!!

sheDhcpServerIpAddress1.name: sheDhcpServerIpAddress1
sheDhcpServerIpAddress1.description: There are three entrys and all three backup each other. Not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified Relay Agent. NOTE: Four possible server ip's with R2.8 maintenance!!

sheDhcpServerIpAddress2.name: sheDhcpServerIpAddress2
sheDhcpServerIpAddress2.description: There are three entrys and all three backup each other. Not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified Relay Agent. NOTE: Four possible server ip's with R2.8 maintenance!!

sheDhcpServerIpAddress3.name: sheDhcpServerIpAddress3
sheDhcpServerIpAddress3.description: There are three entrys and all three backup each other. Not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified Relay Agent. NOTE: Four possible server ip's with R2.8 maintenance!!

sheDhcpServerGateway.name: sheDhcpServerGateway
sheDhcpServerGateway.description: The gateway address of this dhcp provider. Not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified DHCP Relay Agent. Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP route configuration was moved to sheSystemIpRouteTable.

sheDhcpVlanId.name: sheDhcpVlanId
sheDhcpVlanId.description: That points to the VLAN, where the request should be send. A configuration is only in case of simplified DHCP agent possible. For PPPoE and normal DHCP providers the value of sheDhcpVlanId should be 0. That means, no provider vlan for received request's will be used! Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP route configuration was moved to sheSystemIpRouteTable including a possible assignment of vlanId.

sheDhcpRelayAgentIpAddress.name: sheDhcpRelayAgentIpAddress
sheDhcpRelayAgentIpAddress.description: The relay agent IP address is used to set the GIADDR in DHCP messages. With R2.6, it can either be configured to an address that denotes a subscriber's subnet. If not set, the NE will automatically set to the IP of the interface which is used for sending DHCP message to DHCP server. In all cases, a configuration is not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified DHCP Relay Agent.

sheDhcpRelayAgentNetmask.name: sheDhcpRelayAgentNetmask
sheDhcpRelayAgentNetmask.description: The RelayAgent Netmask. Not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified DHCP Relay Agent. Note: This parameter is not longer valid starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP interface configuration was moved to sheSystemIpHostTable.

sheDhcpRelayAgentOption.name: sheDhcpRelayAgentOption
sheDhcpRelayAgentOption.description: Option 82, depends on the Dhcp - Server functionality. If PPPoE is configured also special Options could be implemented. With R2.7 additional options for LineProperty are possible (value 12..23).

sheDhcpCebsMacTranslation.name: sheDhcpCebsMacTranslation
sheDhcpCebsMacTranslation.description: Configuration whether CHADDR in a DHCP packet should be changed or not in CEBS environment. Note: Only valid for DHCP provider configuration (check options) and should always false for PPPoE providers.

sheDhcpRelayAgentMgmt.name: sheDhcpRelayAgentMgmt
sheDhcpRelayAgentMgmt.description: Configuration whether a dhcp provider should be used for mgmt-port relay or not. There can be only one dhcp-provider for mgmt-relay.

sheDhcpInnerVlanId.name: sheDhcpInnerVlanId
sheDhcpInnerVlanId.description: The index of inner-vlan when to forward Requests to the uplink. This vlan tag is used for the inner tag on double tagging mode. A configuration is only in case of simplified DHCP agent possible. For PPPoE and normal DHCP providers the value of sheDhcpVlanId should be 0. That means, no provider vlan for received request's will be used! Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP route configuration was moved to sheSystemIpRouteTable including a possible assignment of vlanId.

sheDhcpBcastTranslationDs.name: sheDhcpBcastTranslationDs
sheDhcpBcastTranslationDs.description: Configuration whether destination address in a DHCP downstream packet should be changed or not. True - use always unicast address False - check broadcast flag from server and use unicast or broadcast address accordingly Note: Only valid for DHCP provider configuration (check options) and should always false for PPPoE providers.

sheDhcpLinePropertyNodeIdentifier.name: sheDhcpLinePropertyNodeIdentifier
sheDhcpLinePropertyNodeIdentifier.description: This parameter defines the name of the access node the DSLAM uses to identifies itself by the provider. New with R2.7.

sheDhcpServerIpAddress4.name: sheDhcpServerIpAddress4
sheDhcpServerIpAddress4.description: Now there are four entrys and all of them backup each other. Not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified Relay Agent. New with R2.8 maintenance.

sheDhcpControlRequest.description: setDhcpAdminState: sheDhcpControlRelayAdminState Depending on the used RelayAgentOption value, not all values are needed. If a PPPoE or simplified option is used, only the values Name and AgentOption are mandatory. createDhcpProviderEntry: sheDhcpControlProfileName sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress1 sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress2 sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress3 sheDhcpControlServerGateway(obsolete) sheDhcpControlVlanId sheDhcpControlRelayAgentOption sheDhcpControlRelayAgentNetmask(obsolete) sheDhcpControlRelayAgentIpAddress sheDhcpControlCebsMacTranslation sheDhcpControlRelayAgentMgmt sheDhcpControlInnerVlanId sheDhcpControlBcastTranslationDs sheDhcpControlLinePropertyNodeIdentifier (new with R2.7) sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress4 (new with R2.8 maintenance) modifyDhcpProviderEntry: sheDhcpControlIndex sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress1 sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress2 sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress3 sheDhcpControlServerGateway(obsolete) sheDhcpControlVlanId sheDhcpControlRelayAgentNetmask(obsolete) sheDhcpControlRelayAgentIpAddress sheDhcpControlRelayAgentOption sheDhcpControlCebsMacTranslation sheDhcpControlRelayAgentMgmt sheDhcpControlInnerVlanId sheDhcpControlBcastTranslationDs sheDhcpControlLinePropertyNodeIdentifier (new with R2.7) sheDhcpControlServerIpAddress4 (new with R2.8 maintenance) deleteDhcpProviderEntry: sheDhcpControlIndex New with R2.8: setDhcpTagForProtocol: sheDhcpControlUseInnerTagForProtocols setDhcpStationMove: sheDhcpControlStationMoveEnabled

sheDhcpControlIndex.description: The table index to be configured.

sheDhcpControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheDhcpControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheDhcpControlRelayRemoteId.name: sheDhcpControlRelayRemoteId
sheDhcpControlRelayRemoteId.description: Per default it is the Mac-Address of the DSLAM (length is 6) to be identified for Option 82. Could be set by operator. (obsoleted in V135)

sheDhcpControlProviderName.name: sheDhcpControlProviderName
sheDhcpControlProviderName.description: Look at table description... Spaces and other special characters (: o) are not allowed!!

sheDhcpControlServerGateway.name: sheDhcpControlServerGateway
sheDhcpControlServerGateway.description: Look at table description... Note: A configuration of this parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP route configuration was moved to sheSystemIpRouteTable.

sheDhcpControlVlanId.name: sheDhcpControlVlanId
sheDhcpControlVlanId.description: Look at table description... Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP route configuration was moved to sheSystemIpRouteTable including a possible assignment of vlanId.

sheDhcpControlRelayAgentIpAddress.name: sheDhcpControlRelayAgentIpAddress
sheDhcpControlRelayAgentIpAddress.description: The relay agent IP address is used to set the GIADDR in DHCP messages. With R2.6, it can either be configured to an address that denotes a subscriber's subnet. If not set, the NE will automatically set to the IP of the interface which is used for sending DHCP message to DHCP server. In all cases, a configuration is not necessary for all PPPoE relay agent options and in case of simplified DHCP Relay Agent.

sheDhcpControlRelayAgentNetmask.name: sheDhcpControlRelayAgentNetmask
sheDhcpControlRelayAgentNetmask.description: The RelayAgent Netmask. Note: A configuration of this parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP interface configuration was moved to sheSystemIpHostTable.

sheDhcpControlRelayAgentOption.name: sheDhcpControlRelayAgentOption
sheDhcpControlRelayAgentOption.description: Look at table description... With R2.7 additional options for LineProperty are possible (value 12..23).

sheDhcpControlCebsMacTranslation.name: sheDhcpControlCebsMacTranslation
sheDhcpControlCebsMacTranslation.description: configuration whether CHADDR in a DHCP packet should be changed or not in CEBS environment. Note: Only valid for DHCP provider configuration (check options) and should always false for PPPoE providers.

sheDhcpControlRelayAgentMgmt.name: sheDhcpControlRelayAgentMgmt
sheDhcpControlRelayAgentMgmt.description: Configuration whether a dhcp provider should be used for mgmt-port relay or not. There can be only one dhcp-provider for mgmt-relay.

sheDhcpControlInnerVlanId.name: sheDhcpControlInnerVlanId
sheDhcpControlInnerVlanId.description: The index of inner-vlan when to forward Dhcp Requests to the uplink. This vlan tag is used for the inner tag on double tagging mode. Only valid for simplified DHCP agent configuration. Look at table description. Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6. The IP route configuration was moved to sheSystemIpRouteTable including a possible assignment of vlanId.

sheDhcpControlBcastTranslationDs.name: sheDhcpControlBcastTranslationDs
sheDhcpControlBcastTranslationDs.description: Configuration whether destination address in a DHCP downstream packet should be changed or not. True - use always unicast address False - check broadcast flag from server and use unicast or broadcast address accordingly Note: Only valid for DHCP provider configuration (check options) and should always false for PPPoE providers.

sheDhcpControlUseInnerTagForProtocols.name: sheDhcpControlUseInnerTagForProtocols
sheDhcpControlUseInnerTagForProtocols.description: Used for configuration of global DHCP and PPPoE useTag settings. BITS { dhcpUseInnerTagTrue(0), pppoeUseInnerTagTrue(1) } If bit is set to 1 the corresponding global parameter is set to true. Support with R2.8.

sheDhcpControlLinePropertyNodeIdentifier.name: sheDhcpControlLinePropertyNodeIdentifier
sheDhcpControlLinePropertyNodeIdentifier.description: This parameter defines the name of the access node the DSLAM uses to identifies itself by the provider. New with R2.7.

sheDhcpControlStationMoveEnabled.name: sheDhcpControlStationMoveEnabled
sheDhcpControlStationMoveEnabled.description: This parameter configure the feature 'station move' for service issues. If enabled, the NE will instantly release all DHCP session informations and possibly learned mac addresses for a certain subscriber line if a 'link down' event for this line was detected. If disabled, all release actions will be done according to FDB aging time and DHCP lease time configuration. New with R2.8.

sheDhcpProviderEntryCreated.name: sheDhcpProviderEntryCreated
sheDhcpProviderEntryCreated.description: A new dhcp provider table entry was created.

sheDhcpProviderEntryModified.name: sheDhcpProviderEntryModified
sheDhcpProviderEntryModified.description: A dhcp provider table entry was modified.

sheDhcpProviderEntryDeleted.name: sheDhcpProviderEntryDeleted
sheDhcpProviderEntryDeleted.description: A dhcp provider table entry was deleted.

sheDhcpRelayAdminStateModified.name: sheDhcpRelayAdminStateModified
sheDhcpRelayAdminStateModified.description: The dhcp relay admin state was modified.

sheDhcpRelayOptionModified.name: sheDhcpRelayOptionModified
sheDhcpRelayOptionModified.description: The dhcp relay option was modified.

sheDhcpRelayRemoteIdModified.name: sheDhcpRelayRemoteIdModified
sheDhcpRelayRemoteIdModified.description: The dhcp relay remote id was modified.

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdAdded.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdAdded
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdAdded.description: The dhcp flood vlanid was added. It becomes obsolete.

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdDeleted.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdDeleted
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdDeleted.description: The dhcp flood vlanid was deleted. It becomes obsolete.

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdModified.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdModified
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdModified.description: The dhcp flood vlanid was modified.

sheDhcpTagForProtocolsModified.name: sheDhcpTagForProtocolsModified
sheDhcpTagForProtocolsModified.description: The dhcp and pppoe global useTag options were modified.

sheDhcpStationMoveEnableModified.name: sheDhcpStationMoveEnableModified
sheDhcpStationMoveEnableModified.description: The dhcp station move enable switch was modified.

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdEntry.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdEntry
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdEntry.description: One entry for each dhcp flood vlanid.

sheDhcpFloodVlanId.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanId
sheDhcpFloodVlanId.description: Index of that table. Will be identical to the used sheVlanIndex.

sheDhcpFloodVlanEnabled.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanEnabled
sheDhcpFloodVlanEnabled.description: Enable or disable a flooding vlan for DHCP packets. The default is false. New with R2.8: Flooding of DHCP or PPPoE packets could now be separatly enabled. The former command switch always both protocol types.

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlStatus.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlStatus
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlStatus.description: The status of a control request

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlTimer.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlTimer
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command. The manager reads this value from the SHE.

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlReqResult.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlReqResult
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlTimeStamp.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlTimeStamp
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command)

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlVlanId.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlVlanId
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlVlanId.description: VLAN ID which is controlled for Dhcp flooding

sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlVlanEnabled.name: sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlVlanEnabled
sheDhcpFloodVlanIdControlVlanEnabled.description: look at table. Expanded with R2.8 maintenance.

sheIgmpMode.name: sheIgmpMode
sheIgmpMode.description: IGMP operation mode can be off proxy That is the general NE igmp on/off switch.

sheIgmpVersion.name: sheIgmpVersion
sheIgmpVersion.description: The version of IGMP which is running on this interface (detected by the NE). The NE uses version 2 as default. If version 1 members are detected on the IP subnet attached to this interface, the NE falls back to version 1. Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.8 The used version should be configured per IGMP profileVlan entry.

sheIgmpMaxJoinedSubscriber.name: sheIgmpMaxJoinedSubscriber
sheIgmpMaxJoinedSubscriber.description: The maximum number of subscribers who can join a multicast group in the system. Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6.

sheIgmpMaxJoinedGroup.name: sheIgmpMaxJoinedGroup
sheIgmpMaxJoinedGroup.description: The maximum number of multicast groups that could be joined in the system.

sheIgmpVlanTranslationMode.name: sheIgmpVlanTranslationMode
sheIgmpVlanTranslationMode.description: Configure VLAN translation mode for the system. 1 is inner tagged, 2 is outer tagged, default configuration is inner. This configuration is only functions when system is configured in double tagging mode. New with SHE R.8.

sheIgmpVlanDoubleTaggingMode.name: sheIgmpVlanDoubleTaggingMode
sheIgmpVlanDoubleTaggingMode.description: Configure provider VLAN tagging mode for the system, 1 is inner, 2 is outer, default configuration is outer. This configuration is only functions when system is configured in double tagging mode. New with SHE R.8.

sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlRequest.name: sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlRequest
sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlRequest.description: New with SHE R.8. setIgmpTagMode: sheIgmpControlVlanTranslationMode sheIgmpControlVlanDoubleTaggingMode

sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlStatus.name: sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlStatus
sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlTimeStamp
sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlReqResult
sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlTimer.name: sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlTimer
sheIgmpDoubleTaggingControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheIgmpControlVlanTranslationMode.name: sheIgmpControlVlanTranslationMode
sheIgmpControlVlanTranslationMode.description: Configure VLAN translation mode for the system, 1 is inner tagged, 2 is outer tagged, default configuration is inner. This configuration is only functions when system is configured in double tagging mode. New with SHE R.8.

sheIgmpControlVlanDoubleTaggingMode.name: sheIgmpControlVlanDoubleTaggingMode
sheIgmpControlVlanDoubleTaggingMode.description: Configure provider VLAN tagging mode for the system, 1 is inner, 2 is outer, default configuration is outer. This configuration is only functions when system is configured in double tagging mode. New with SHE R.8.

sheIgmpProfileTable.name: sheIgmpProfileTable
sheIgmpProfileTable.description: The table has one provider entry. It contains the provider VLAN and the host and querier settings.

sheIgmpProfileEntry.name: sheIgmpProfileEntry
sheIgmpProfileEntry.description: In first release we will only support one table entry.

sheIgmpProviderProfileName.name: sheIgmpProviderProfileName
sheIgmpProviderProfileName.description: Name for easy profile handling. Spaces and other special characters (: o) are not allowed!!

sheIgmpProviderProxyIpAddress.name: sheIgmpProviderProxyIpAddress
sheIgmpProviderProxyIpAddress.description: The source IP address used by the IGMP proxy for join and leave messages in upstream direction and for queries in downstream direction.

sheIgmpProviderRobustness.name: sheIgmpProviderRobustness
sheIgmpProviderRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses. The Robustness Variable MUST NOT be zero, and SHOULD NOT be one.

sheIgmpProviderQueryInterval.name: sheIgmpProviderQueryInterval
sheIgmpProviderQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets (downstream) are transmitted on this interface.

sheIgmpProviderQueryResponseInterval.name: sheIgmpProviderQueryResponseInterval
sheIgmpProviderQueryResponseInterval.description: The Max Response Time inserted into the periodic General Queries. When the subscriber host doesn't respond to IGMP query messages, it is unsubscribed from the multicast group. It must be less than the Query Interval.

sheIgmpProviderStartupQueryInterval.name: sheIgmpProviderStartupQueryInterval
sheIgmpProviderStartupQueryInterval.description: The startup frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets (downstream) are transmitted on this interface.

sheIgmpProviderStartupQueryCount.name: sheIgmpProviderStartupQueryCount
sheIgmpProviderStartupQueryCount.description: The Startup Query Count is the number of Queries sent out on startup, separated by the Startup Query Interval.

sheIgmpProviderLastMemberQueryInterval.name: sheIgmpProviderLastMemberQueryInterval
sheIgmpProviderLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages. This value may be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network. A reduced value results in reduced time to detect the loss of the last member of a group. The value of this object is irrelevant if igmpInterfaceVersion is 1.

sheIgmpProviderLastMemberQueryCount.name: sheIgmpProviderLastMemberQueryCount
sheIgmpProviderLastMemberQueryCount.description: The Last Member Query Count is the number of Group-Specific Queries sent before the router assumes there are no local members.

sheIgmpProviderImmediateLeave.name: sheIgmpProviderImmediateLeave
sheIgmpProviderImmediateLeave.description: If immediate leave is disabled and the client sends a leave message, the switch sends a query message to the client. When there is no response from the client, it is deleted from the multicast group. If immediate leave is enabled, the client is deleted from the multicast group when the switch receives the leave message. Note: Not longer configurable with R2.8.

sheIgmpProviderUnsolicitedReportInterval.name: sheIgmpProviderUnsolicitedReportInterval
sheIgmpProviderUnsolicitedReportInterval.description: The Unsolicited Report Interval is the time between repetitions of a host's initial report of membership in a group (upstream).

sheIgmpProviderVersion1RouterTimeout.name: sheIgmpProviderVersion1RouterTimeout
sheIgmpProviderVersion1RouterTimeout.description: The Version 1 Router Present Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Version 1 Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages. The time until the local router will assume that there are no longer any IGMP version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this interface. Upon hearing any IGMPv1 Membership Report, this value is loaded to a timer. While the timer is running, the local router ignores any IGMPv2 Leave messages for this group that it receives on this interface. With R2.8 and support of IGMPv3 these attribute means OlderVersionRouterTimeout.

sheIgmpProviderVersion1RouterPresentTime.name: sheIgmpProviderVersion1RouterPresentTimeout
sheIgmpProviderVersion1RouterPresentTime.description: The time remaining until a host will assume that there are no longer any IGMP version 1 routers on the IP subnet attached to this interface. Upon hearing any Version 1 Query, this value is reset to the group membership timer. While this time remaining is non-zero, it may not send any IGMPv2 messages. The time remaining until the local router will assume that there are no longer any IGMP version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this interface. Upon hearing any IGMPv1 Membership Report, this value is reset to the group membership timer. While this time remaining is non-zero, the local router ignores any IGMPv2 Leave messages for this group that it receives on this interface. With R2.8 and support of IGMPv3 these attribute means OlderVersionRouterPresentTimeout.

sheIgmpProviderVlanMulticastLimitation.name: sheIgmpProviderVlanMulticastLimitation
sheIgmpProviderVlanMulticastLimitation.description: Configures all possible multicast addresses for IGMP on a per VLAN basis. This parameter indicates whether this IGMP provider have the limitation on the multicast group/packages or not. Value can be true(1) or false(2). False means all subscriber can join all multicast streams through to this whole VLAN if they are member of this vlan (unlimited access). True is the default state and means only configured groups/packages could be joined (limited access).

sheIgmpProviderMcastBandwithLimit.name: sheIgmpProviderMcastBandwithLimit
sheIgmpProviderMcastBandwithLimit.description: This is the configured multicast bandwith limitation per provider. The value 65535 (0xFFFF) is a special value and means unlimited access for this provider (switch off feature AC - admission control - default). New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpProviderDefaultChannelBandwith.name: sheIgmpProviderDefaultChannelBandwith
sheIgmpProviderDefaultChannelBandwith.description: This parameter has a range of 0..500 representing the default channel bandwith with a granularity of 100kBits. When a non-premium channel is registered, its channel bandwidth will adopt the default bandwith. New parameter with SHE R2.8

sheIgmpProviderControlRequest.name: sheIgmpProviderControlRequest
sheIgmpProviderControlRequest.description: setIgmpMode: sheIgmpProviderControlMode setIgmpMaxJoinedSubscribers: (Note: Not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6.) sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedSubscribers setIgmpMaxJoinedGroup: sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedGroup createIgmpProviderEntry: sheIgmpProviderControlProfileName sheIgmpProviderControlProxyIpAddress sheIgmpProviderControlRoboustness sheIgmpProviderControlQueryInterval sheIgmpProviderControlQueryResponseInterval sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryInterval sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryCount sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryInterval sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryCount sheIgmpProviderControlImmediateLeave sheIgmpProviderControlUnsolicitedReportInterval sheIgmpProviderControlVersion1RouterTimeout sheIgmpProviderControlVlanMulticastLimitation modifyIgmpProviderEntry: sheIgmpProviderControlIndex sheIgmpProviderControlProfileName sheIgmpProviderControlProxyIpAddress sheIgmpProviderControlRoboustness sheIgmpProviderControlQueryInterval sheIgmpProviderControlQueryResponseInterval sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryInterval sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryCount sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryInterval sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryCount sheIgmpProviderControlImmediateLeave sheIgmpProviderControlUnsolicitedReportInterval sheIgmpProviderControlVersion1RouterTimeout sheIgmpProviderControlVlanMulticastLimitation deleteIgmpProviderEntry: sheIgmpProviderControlIndex New with SHE R2.8: setIgmpProviderChannelAdmission (743): sheIgmpProviderControlIndex sheIgmpProviderControlMcastBandwithLimit sheIgmpProviderControlDefaultChannelBandwith

sheIgmpProviderControlStatus.name: sheIgmpProviderControlStatus
sheIgmpProviderControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheIgmpProviderControlTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpProviderControlTimeStamp
sheIgmpProviderControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpProviderControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpProviderControlReqResult
sheIgmpProviderControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpProviderControlTimer.name: sheIgmpProviderControlTimer
sheIgmpProviderControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheIgmpProviderControlIndex.name: sheIgmpProviderControlIndex
sheIgmpProviderControlIndex.description: index of sheIgmpProviderTable parameter for - modifyIgmpProviderEntry - deleteIgmpProviderEntry - setIgmpProviderEntrySourceList

sheIgmpProviderControlMode.name: sheIgmpProviderControlMode
sheIgmpProviderControlMode.description: IGMP operation mode can be off proxy parameter for - setIgmpMode That is the general NE igmp on/off switch.

sheIgmpProviderControlProfileName.name: sheIgmpProviderControlProfileName
sheIgmpProviderControlProfileName.description: Name for easy profile handling. Spaces and other special characters (: o) are not allowed!! parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlProxyIpAddress.name: sheIgmpProviderControlProxyIpAddress
sheIgmpProviderControlProxyIpAddress.description: The source IP address used by the IGMP proxy for join and leave messages in upstream direction and for queries in downstream direction. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlRobustness.name: sheIgmpProviderControlRobustness
sheIgmpProviderControlRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses. The Robustness Variable MUST NOT be zero, and SHOULD NOT be one. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlQueryInterval.name: sheIgmpProviderControlQueryInterval
sheIgmpProviderControlQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets (downstream) are transmitted on this interface. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlQueryResponseInter.name: sheIgmpProviderControlQueryResponseInterval
sheIgmpProviderControlQueryResponseInter.description: The Max Response Time inserted into the periodic General Queries. When the subscriber host doesn't respond to IGMP query messages, it is unsubscribed from the multicast group. It must be less than the Query Interval. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryInterv.name: sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryInterval
sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryInterv.description: The startup frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets (downstream) are transmitted on this interface. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryCount.name: sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryCount
sheIgmpProviderControlStartupQueryCount.description: The Startup Query Count is the number of Queries sent out on startup, separated by the Startup Query Interval. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryInt.name: sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryInterval
sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryInt.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages. This value may be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network. A reduced value results in reduced time to detect the loss of the last member of a group. The value of this object is irrelevant if igmpInterfaceVersion is 1. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryCou.name: sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryCount
sheIgmpProviderControlLastMemberQueryCou.description: The Last Member Query Count is the number of Group-Specific Queries sent before the router assumes there are no local members. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlImmediateLeave.name: sheIgmpProviderControlImmediateLeave
sheIgmpProviderControlImmediateLeave.description: If immediate leave is disabled and the client sends a leave message, the switch sends a query message to the client. When there is no response from the client, it is deleted from the multicast group. If immediate leave is enabled, the client is deleted from the multicast group when the switch receives the leave message. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry Note: Not longer configurable with R2.8.

sheIgmpProviderControlUnsolicitedReportI.name: sheIgmpProviderControlUnsolicitedReportInterval
sheIgmpProviderControlUnsolicitedReportI.description: The Unsolicited Report Interval is the time between repetitions of a host's initial report of membership in a group (upstream). parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry

sheIgmpProviderControlVersion1RouterTime.name: sheIgmpProviderControlVersion1RouterTimeout
sheIgmpProviderControlVersion1RouterTime.description: The Version 1 Router Present Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Version 1 Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages. The time until the local router will assume that there are no longer any IGMP version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this interface. Upon hearing any IGMPv1 Membership Report, this value is loaded to a timer. While the timer is running, the local router ignores any IGMPv2 Leave messages for this group that it receives on this interface. parameter for - createIgmpProviderEntry - modifyIgmpProviderEntry With R2.8 and support of IGMPv3 these attribute means OlderVersionRouterTimeout.

sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedSubscribe.name: sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedSubscriber
sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedSubscribe.description: The maximum number of joined subscribers in the system. Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6.

sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedGroup.name: sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedGroup
sheIgmpProviderControlMaxJoinedGroup.description: The maximum number of multicast groups that could be joined in the system.

sheIgmpProviderControlMcastBandwithLimit.name: sheIgmpProviderControlMcastBandwithLimit
sheIgmpProviderControlMcastBandwithLimit.description: This is the configured multicast bandwith limitation per provider. The value 655353 (0xFFFF) is a special value and means unlimited access for this provider (switch off feature AC - admission control). New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpProviderControlDefaultChannelBand.name: sheIgmpProviderControlDefaultChannelBandwith
sheIgmpProviderControlDefaultChannelBand.description: This parameter has a range of 0..500 representing the default channel bandwith with a granularity of 100kBits. When a non-premium channel is registered, its channel bandwidth will adopt the default bandwith. New parameter with SHE R2.8

sheIgmpProfileVlanTable.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanTable
sheIgmpProfileVlanTable.description: The table assigns a VLANs for multicast traffic to multicast provider profiles. Both a Vlan and a profile can be assigned only once.

sheIgmpProfileVlanEntry.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanEntry
sheIgmpProfileVlanEntry.description: A table entry assigns a VLAN for multicast traffic to a multicast provider profile. Both a Vlan and a profile can be assigned only once.

sheIgmpProfileVlanVlanId.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanVlanId
sheIgmpProfileVlanVlanId.description: The provider specific Vlan for multicast traffic. The sheVlanIndex for that Vlan.

sheIgmpProfileVlanMcastEgressPorts.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanMcastEgressPorts
sheIgmpProfileVlanMcastEgressPorts.description: List of all fully configured subscriber ports of this multicast VLAN. The list is updated whenever any part of the chain bridgePort->MCastPackage->IgmpGroup changes. The octet string is a list of pairs of octets each identifying an sheBridgePortIndex. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheIgmpProfileVlanInnerVlanId.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanInnerVlanId
sheIgmpProfileVlanInnerVlanId.description: An inner vlanid for this igmp provider vlan. It is used in double tagging mode when sending IGMP packets to uplink. It is useless besides double tagging mode and could be 0 in that case.

sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pPriority.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pPriority.description: The priority of an IGMP query that is inserted in vlan tag when a querier sends it to subscribers.

sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pReportPriority.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pReportPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pReportPriority.description: The priority of an IGMP report that is inserted in vlan tag when a host sends it to router.

sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pInnerPriority.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pInnerPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pInnerPriority.description: The inner priority of an IGMP query that is inserted in inner vlan tag when a querier sends a query to subscribers. This attribute is used only for double tagging mode.

sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pInnerReportPriori.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pInnerReportPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanDot1pInnerReportPriori.description: The priority of an IGMP report that is inserted in inner vlan tag when a host sends a report to router. This attribute is used only for double tagging mode.

sheIgmpProfileVlanForkingMode.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanForkingMode
sheIgmpProfileVlanForkingMode.description: IGMP forking function enabled will send the original IGMP messages with actual MAC address of the clients (e.g. STB) and the corresponding/preserved customer VLAN ID towards the BRAS/Edge Router regardless of IGMP proxy configuration/operation. Possible values: noForking(0), ipoeForking(1), pppoeForking(2)

sheIgmpProfileVlanOuterVlanId.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanOuterVlanId
sheIgmpProfileVlanOuterVlanId.description: An outer vlanid for this igmp provider vlan. It is used in double tagging mode when sending IGMP packets to uplink. It is useless besides double tagging mode and could be 0 in that case. New with R2.8.

sheIgmpProfileVlanVersion.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanVersion
sheIgmpProfileVlanVersion.description: Configure the supported IGMP version for that provider specific vlan. IGMP frames of wrong version should be silently discarded. New parameter with SHE R2.8

sheIgmpProfileVlanASMStatus.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanASMStatus
sheIgmpProfileVlanASMStatus.description: Igmp provider ASM (any source multicast)status. When enabled, any source multicast is allowed for the provider, when disabled, any source multicast is not permitted for the provider. Default value is Enable. New parameter with SHE R2.8

sheIgmpProfileVlanCxUSnoopingState.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanCxUSnoopingState
sheIgmpProfileVlanCxUSnoopingState.description: It indicates whether IGMP CXU snooping mode is enabled on provider. Value 0 is disable; value 1 is enable. Default value is disable. New parameter with SHE R2.8

sheIgmpProfileVlanDefaultSourceIdList.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanDefaultSourceIdList
sheIgmpProfileVlanDefaultSourceIdList.description: This parameter contains a list of indeces which points to valid entries of the sheIgmpSourceIpAddressTable. Each octet represents one index value. The list could be empty (default). If the configured sheIgmpMcastChannelSourceId of related group's points to index with IP address 0.0.0.0 (wildcard configuration, ASM), any IGMP report message in network direction is sent as IGMv3 ASM report. If the defaultList contains entries pointing to other non-zero IP-addresses, those (all of them) are used to generate an IGMPv3 SSM report packet in network direction. In case of IGMP provider mode IGMPv3 or IGMPv3Compatible the default IP list is checked with channel as key for any received ASM packet to determine the transmission mode (ASM,SSM) and source address for packets sent in network direction. This configuration is not valid for IGMPv2 provider mode. This configuration here will be outvoted by a similar configuration for the related IgmpGroup. New parameter with SHE R2.8 maintenance.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlRequest.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlRequest
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlRequest.description: createIgmpProfileVlanEntry: - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlIndex - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlVlanId - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pReportPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pReportInnerPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlInnerVlanId - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlOuterVlanId (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlVersion (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlASMStatus (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlCxuSnoopingState (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDefaultSourceIdList (new with R2.8 maintenance) deleteIgmpProfileVlanEntry: - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlIndex modifyIgmpProfileVlanDot1p: - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlIndex - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pReportPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pReportInnerPriority - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlInnerVlanId - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlOuterVlanId (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlVersion (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlASMStatus (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlCxuSnoopingState (new with R2.8) - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDefaultSourceIdList (new with R2.8 maintenance) R2.4 only modifyIgmpProfileVlanForkingMode: - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlIndex - sheIgmpProfileVlanControlForkingMode

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlStatus.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlStatus
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlReqResult
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlTimer.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlTimer
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlIndex.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlIndex
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlIndex.description: The index sheIgmpProviderIndex of the provider specific multicast profile. parameter for - createIgmpProfileVlanEntry - deleteIgmpProfileVlanEntry

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlVlanId.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlVlanId
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlVlanId.description: The provider specific Vlan for multicast traffic. The sheVlanIndex for that Vlan. parameter for - deleteIgmpProfileVlanEntry

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlInnerVlanId.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlInnerVlanId
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlInnerVlanId.description: An inner vlanid for this igmp provider vlan or 0 if not used.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pPriority.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pPriority.description: The priority of an IGMP query that is inserted in vlan tag when a querier sends it to subscribers.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pReportPrio.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pReportPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pReportPrio.description: The priority of an IGMP report that is inserted in vlan tag when a host sends it to router.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerPrior.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerPrior.description: The inner priority of an IGMP query that is inserted in inner vlan tag when a querier sends a query to subscribers. This attribute is used only for double tagging mode.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerRepor.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerReportPriority
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDot1pInnerRepor.description: The priority of an IGMP report that is inserted in inner vlan tag when a host sends a report to router. This attribute is used only for double tagging mode.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlForkingMode.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlForkingMode
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlForkingMode.description: When it's set to 0, it means no forking, when set to 1 it means forking mode is IPoE forking, when set to 2, PPPoE forking is used for the provider

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlOuterVlanId.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlOuterVlanId
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlOuterVlanId.description: An outer vlanid for this igmp provider vlan or 0 if not used.

sheIgmpProviderControlVersion.name: sheIgmpProviderControlVersion
sheIgmpProviderControlVersion.description: Configure the supported IGMP version for that provider specific vlan. IGMP frames of wrong version should be silently discarded. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpProviderControlASMStatus.name: sheIgmpProviderControlASMStatus
sheIgmpProviderControlASMStatus.description: Igmp provider ASM (any source multicast)status. When enabled, any source multicast is allowed for the provider, when disabled, any source multicast is not permitted for the provider. Default value is Enable. parameter for - createIgmpProfileVlanEntry: - modifyIgmpProfileVlanDot1p: New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlCxUSnoopingStat.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlCxUSnoopingState
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlCxUSnoopingStat.description: It indicates whether IGMP CXU snooping mode is enabled on provider. Value 0 is disable; value 1 is enable. parameter for - createIgmpProfileVlanEntry: - modifyIgmpProfileVlanDot1p: New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDefaultSourceId.name: sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDefaultSourceIdList
sheIgmpProfileVlanControlDefaultSourceId.description: look at table New parameter with SHE R2.8 maintenance.

sheIgmpGroupTable.name: sheIgmpGroupTable
sheIgmpGroupTable.description: The table contains entries for multicast groups. A group has a specific multicast address, belongs to a provider and to a multicast group package.

sheIgmpGroupEntry.name: sheIgmpGroupEntry
sheIgmpGroupEntry.description: One entry for each Igmp-Group. If IGMPv3 is running, each table entry represent a single channel configuration.

sheIgmpGroupIpAddress.name: sheIgmpGroupIpAddress
sheIgmpGroupIpAddress.description: The used Multicast IP-Address. If these Address is set to 00000000, it should work as a * wildcard configuration, it means an any group (S,*) channel.

sheIgmpGroupName.name: sheIgmpGroupName
sheIgmpGroupName.description: A unique name for this multicast group. Spaces and other special characters (: o) are not allowed!!

sheIgmpGroupProviderId.name: sheIgmpGroupProviderId
sheIgmpGroupProviderId.description: That is the index of the corresponding sheIgmpProviderTable entry.

sheIgmpGroupMcastGroupPackageList.name: sheIgmpGroupMcastGroupPackageList
sheIgmpGroupMcastGroupPackageList.description: That is a list of available corresponding indices of the sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageTable where this group is a member. Each index has 16 bit. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheIgmpGroupJoinedPortsList.name: sheIgmpGroupJoinedPortsList
sheIgmpGroupJoinedPortsList.description: List of subscribers currently subscribing this multicast group. The octet string is a list of pairs of octets each identifying an sheBridgePortIndex. The least significant byte is the second octet. A change in this list will not be reported by a trap.

sheIgmpGroupLastMembershipReport.name: sheIgmpGroupLastMembershipReport
sheIgmpGroupLastMembershipReport.description: Time since the last membership report has been sent upstream by the proxy for this multicast group.

sheIgmpGroupLastLeaveMessage.name: sheIgmpGroupLastLeaveMessage
sheIgmpGroupLastLeaveMessage.description: Time since the last leave group message has been sent upstream by the proxy for this multicast group.

sheIgmpGroupSuppliedCardList.name: sheIgmpGroupSuppliedCardList
sheIgmpGroupSuppliedCardList.description: List of entPhysIndices currently receiving data of this multicast group. The octet string is a list of pairs of octets each identifying an entPhysIndex for that card. The least significant byte is the second octet. A change in this list will not be reported by a trap.

sheIgmpGroupIsStatic.name: sheIgmpGroupIsStatic
sheIgmpGroupIsStatic.description: Enable or disable static multicast group configuration.

sheIgmpMcastChannelSourceId.name: sheIgmpMcastChannelSourceId
sheIgmpMcastChannelSourceId.description: This is a index which points to valid entry of the sheIgmpSourceIpAddressTable. If the source IP of the index is 0.0.0.0 (default), it should work as a '*' wildcard configuration and no restriction of possible source ip addresses are made (*,G). In case of IGMP mode iGMPv3 or iGMPv3Compatible ASM will be used. This setting is also valid for mode iGMPv2 usage. The configuration of other source IP's is only valid if iGMPv3 or iGMPv3Compatible mode is running. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpMcastChannelBandwith.name: sheIgmpMcastChannelBandwith
sheIgmpMcastChannelBandwith.description: The bandwith of this channel, with a range of 0..500 representing the bandwith with a granularity of 100kBits. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpMcastChannelDefaultSourceIdList.name: sheIgmpMcastChannelDefaultSourceIdList
sheIgmpMcastChannelDefaultSourceIdList.description: This parameter contains a list of indeces which points to valid entries of the sheIgmpSourceIpAddressTable. Each octet represents one index value. The list could be empty (default). If the configured sheIgmpMcastChannelSourceId of these group points to index with IP address 0.0.0.0 (wildcard configuration, ASM), any IGMP report message in network direction is sent as IGMv3 ASM report. If the defaultList contains entries pointing to other non-zero IP-addresses, those (all of them) are used to generate an IGMPv3 SSM report packet in network direction. In case of IGMP provider mode IGMPv3 or IGMPv3Compatible the default IP list is checked with channel as key for any received ASM packet to determine the transmission mode (ASM,SSM) and source address for packets sent in network direction. This configuration is not valid for IGMPv2 provider mode. This configuration here will outvote a similar configuration for the corresponding IgmpProvider. New parameter with SHE R2.8 maintenance.

sheIgmpGroupControlIsStatic.name: sheIgmpGroupControlIsStatic
sheIgmpGroupControlIsStatic.description: Enable or disable static multicast group configuration.

sheIgmpMcastChannelControlSourceId.description: look at table. New parameter with SHE R2.8.

sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageTable.description: The table contains entry's they combines multicast groups to a multicast group package.

sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageEntry.name: sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageEntry
sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageEntry.description: One entry for each multicast group package.

sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageName.name: sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageName
sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageName.description: That should be a descriptional name. Spaces and other special characters (: o) are not allowed!!

sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageGroupList.name: sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageGroupList
sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageGroupList.description: That is a list of pairs of octets each identifying a corresponding index of the sheIgmpGroupTable. It shows the groups that are members of the package. The list is updated by the NE when the package list of a group is modified. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageControlStatus.name: sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageControlStatus
sheIgmpMcastGroupPackageControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheIgmpPortGroupsTable.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsTable
sheIgmpPortGroupsTable.description: For the subscriber bridge ports (first table index is sheBridgePortIndex) the table has entries for all multicast groups a port has currently joined. Because IgmpV3 allow the configuration of wildcard's for used multicast and/or source IP address, R2.8 maintenance modify the second table index to a free running index and add parameter to show the used multicast IP address.

sheIgmpPortGroupsEntry.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsEntry
sheIgmpPortGroupsEntry.description: If IGMPv3 is running, it represent a joined channel!

sheIgmpPortGroupsStpIpAddress.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsStpIpAddress
sheIgmpPortGroupsStpIpAddress.description: The IP address of the subsribers host (set top box) that has joined the multicast group. Each Ip address is a set of 4 octets. Expanded with R2.8: If Igmpv3 is running up to five boxes could be listed here.

sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeFirstMembRep.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeFirstMembRep
sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeFirstMembRep.description: The time when the first membership report for the joined multicast group has been received from the subscriber. Note: Set to obsolete with R2.8 - no valid information could be returned!

sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeLastMembRep.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeLastMembRep
sheIgmpPortGroupsTimeLastMembRep.description: The time when the last membership report for the joined multicast group has been received from the subscriber.

sheIgmpPortGroupsFiltermode.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsFiltermode
sheIgmpPortGroupsFiltermode.description: This parameter may be either INCLUDE or EXCLUDE. In INCLUDE mode, reception of packets sent to the specified multicast address is requested *only* from those IP source address listed in the source-id parameter. In EXCLUDE mode, reception of packets sent to the given multicast address is requested from all IP source addresses *except* those listed in the source-id parameter. New parameter with SHE R2.8 and only valid for IGMPv3.

sheIgmpPortGroupsSourceId.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsSourceId
sheIgmpPortGroupsSourceId.description: This is an IP unicast addresses from which multicast reception is desired or not desired, depending on the filter mode. IP address entry consist of 4 Octets and should be a subset or identical to the corresponding sheIgmpMcastChannelSourceId of the joined group. New parameter with SHE R2.8 and only valid for IGMPv3.

sheIgmpPortGroupsIpAddress.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsIpAddress
sheIgmpPortGroupsIpAddress.description: The used Multicast IP-Address of the joined group. New parameter with SHE R2.8 maintenance.

sheIgmpPortGroupsIndex.name: sheIgmpPortGroupsIndex
sheIgmpPortGroupsIndex.description: The new second tableIndex starting with R2.8 maintenance. It is a free running Index which show the amount of actual joined groups by this subscriber.

sheIgmpMaxJoinedSubscriberModified.description: The general IGMP MaxJoinedSubscriber-Value has been modified by the operator. Note: This parameter is not longer supported starting with release SHE R2.6.

sheIgmpFloodVlanCreated.description: An entry in the sheIgmpFloodVlanTable was created by the operator.

sheIgmpPmObjectTable.description: The table holds all IGMP PM objects existing in the NE.

sheIgmpPmObjectEntry.name: sheIgmpPmObjectEntry
sheIgmpPmObjectEntry.description: A table entry shows the multicast group a PM object is related to.

sheIgmpPmObjectIndex.name: sheIgmpPmObjectIndex
sheIgmpPmObjectIndex.description: Unique index for IGMP PM objects existing in the NE. One multicast group can have one PM object, including both interval types.

sheIgmpPmObjectGroupIndex.name: sheIgmpPmObjectGroupIndex
sheIgmpPmObjectGroupIndex.description: Index sheIgmpGroupIndex of the sheIgmpGroupTable selects the multicast group a PM object is related to.

sheIgmpPmCurrentTable.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentTable
sheIgmpPmCurrentTable.description: This table contains the entries for Performance Monitoring for multicast groups of the current 15 minute interval and the current day.

sheIgmpPmCurrentEntry.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentEntry
sheIgmpPmCurrentEntry.description: An entry describing the current PM data of a multicast group for a certain interval type. Indices are sheIgmpPmObjectIndex and sheIgmpPmCurrentIntervalType.

sheIgmpPmCurrentIntervalType.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentIntervalType
sheIgmpPmCurrentIntervalType.description: This attribute is used to select between the 15 min or the day accumulation types.

sheIgmpPmCurrentAdminState.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentAdminState
sheIgmpPmCurrentAdminState.description: This read-write attribute is used to activate (up) and deactivate (down) performance monitoring for the multicast group and interval type.

sheIgmpPmCurrentSuspectFlag.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentSuspectFlag
sheIgmpPmCurrentSuspectFlag.description: This read-only attribute will be set to indicate that troubles arose during an interval and that the counter values are suspect and incomplete.

sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntrySize.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntrySize
sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntrySize.description: The number of history entries configured for the multicast group and interval type. This attribute is used for history data collection. The default value is 1 and means at least one history entry is desired.

sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntriesAvailable.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntriesAvailable
sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntriesAvailable.description: This read-only attribute indicates how many HistEntries are already available. The range of values is between 0 and sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntrySize. Thereby 0 means that this entry is not valid.

sheIgmpPmCurrentElapsedTime.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentElapsedTime
sheIgmpPmCurrentElapsedTime.description: This read-only attribute represents the difference between the current time and the start of the present summary interval. Units are seconds when 15 minute interval is selected or minutes for day interval. (Note: accurate to the sample time interval).

sheIgmpPmCurrentMembershipReportsFromHos.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentMembershipReportsFromHost
sheIgmpPmCurrentMembershipReportsFromHos.description: Successful join requests for the multicast group received from the subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmCurrentPeakMembershipReportsFro.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentPeakMembershipReportsFromHost
sheIgmpPmCurrentPeakMembershipReportsFro.description: Peak of successful join requests per second for the multicast group received from the subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmCurrentTimeOfPeakGroupLeaves.description: Time and date of the peak of IGMP group leave messages per second for the multicast group received from the subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmCurrentGroupLeavesToRouter.name: sheIgmpPmCurrentGroupLeavesToRouter
sheIgmpPmCurrentGroupLeavesToRouter.description: IGMP group leave messages for the multicast group sent to the router.

sheIgmpPmCurrentPeakMulticastLeaves.description: The peak number of the multicast tree leaves (branches) for the multicast group shows the peak number of joined subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmHistoryTableTable.description: A table containing all IGMP PM history data. Indices of the table are the PM object, the interval type and the record number.

sheIgmpPmHistoryTableEntry.name: sheIgmpPmHistoryTableEntry
sheIgmpPmHistoryTableEntry.description: An entry describing the history PM data of a multicast group for a certain interval type and record number.

sheIgmpPmHistoryIntervalType.name: sheIgmpPmHistoryIntervalType
sheIgmpPmHistoryIntervalType.description: This attribute is used to select between the 15 min or the day accumulation types.

sheIgmpPmHistoryEntryNumber.name: sheIgmpPmHistoryEntryNumber
sheIgmpPmHistoryEntryNumber.description: This attribute is an index used to address the PM history entry. Entry 1 is the most recent. The range of values is between 1 and sheIgmpPmCurrentHistEntrySize.

sheIgmpPmHistorySuspectFlag.name: sheIgmpPmHistorySuspectFlag
sheIgmpPmHistorySuspectFlag.description: This read-only attribute will be set to indicate that troubles arose during an interval and that the counter values are suspect and incomplete.

sheIgmpPmHistoryPeriodEndTime.name: sheIgmpPmHistoryPeriodEndTime
sheIgmpPmHistoryPeriodEndTime.description: Date/time at the end of the selected interval.

sheIgmpPmHistoryTimeOfPeakMembershipRepo.description: Time and date of the peak of successful join requests per second for the multicast group received from the subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmHistoryGroupLeavesFromHost.description: IGMP group leave messages for the multicast group received from the subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmHistoryPeakGroupLeavesFromHost.name: sheIgmpPmHistoryPeakGroupLeavesFromHost
sheIgmpPmHistoryPeakGroupLeavesFromHost.description: Peak of IGMP group leave messages per second for the multicast group received from the subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmHistoryTimeOfPeakGroupLeaves.name: sheIgmpPmHistoryTimeOfPeakGroupLeaves
sheIgmpPmHistoryTimeOfPeakGroupLeaves.description: Time and date of the peak of IGMP group leave messages per second for the multicast group received from the subscriber ports.

sheIgmpPmHistoryMembershipReportsToRoute.description: Successful join requests for the multicast group sent to the router.

sheIgmpPmHistoryGroupLeavesToRouter.description: IGMP group leave messages for the multicast group sent to the router.

sheIgmpPmControlIntervalType.name: sheIgmpPmControlIntervalType
sheIgmpPmControlIntervalType.description: This attribute is used to select between the 15 min or the day accumulation types. parameter for modifyPmObject

sheIgmpPmControlHistEntrySize.description: The number of history entries configured for the multicast group and interval type. This attribute is used for history data collection. The default value is 1 and means at least one history entry is desired. In case of PM object creation the number of 15 min entries is set and the number of 24 h entries is always 1. parameter for createPmObject modifyPmObject

sheIgmpPmControlRemainingHistoryEntries.description: The number of history entries which are still available for the PM data collection within the NE. The memory for PM data is limited.
